WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.520 --> 00:00:02.020
<font color="#ffff00" size=14>www.moviesubtitles.org</font>

2
00:00:42.820 --> 00:00:44.822
<i>Report to your stations immediately.</i>

3
00:00:44.980 --> 00:00:47.741
<i>This is not a drill. We are under attack!</i>

4
00:00:49.140 --> 00:00:51.108
<i>We are under attack!</i>

5
00:01:52.220 --> 00:01:54.507
- Shit!
- Language!

6
00:01:54.620 --> 00:01:56.224
Jarvis. what's the view from upstairs?

7
00:01:56.620 --> 00:02:00.306
<i>The central building is protected
by some kind of energy shield.</i>

8
00:02:00.820 --> 00:02:04.542
<i>Strucker's technology is well beyond
any other Hydra base we've taken.</i>

9
00:02:07.380 --> 00:02:08.950
Loki's sceptre must be here.

10
00:02:09.580 --> 00:02:11.460
Strucker couldn't mount this defence
without it.

11
00:02:12.180 --> 00:02:13.750
At long last.

12
00:02:25.220 --> 00:02:27.427
"At long last"
is lasting a little long. boys.

13
00:02:32.340 --> 00:02:34.866
Yeah. I think we lost
the element of surprise.

14
00:02:36.420 --> 00:02:38.627
Wait a second.
No one else is gonna deal with the fact

15
00:02:38.780 --> 00:02:40.544
that Cap just said "Language"?

16
00:02:40.700 --> 00:02:42.225
I know.

17
00:02:47.260 --> 00:02:49.547
Just slipped out.

18
00:02:55.620 --> 00:02:57.384
Who gave the order to attack?

19
00:02:57.500 --> 00:02:59.787
<i>Herr</i> Strucker. it's the Avengers.

20
00:02:59.940 --> 00:03:02.784
They landed in the far woods.
The perimeter guard panicked.

21
00:03:02.940 --> 00:03:04.863
They have to be after the sceptre.

22
00:03:06.100 --> 00:03:08.467
- Can we hold them?
- They're the Avengers.

23
00:03:08.580 --> 00:03:10.184
Deploy the rest of the tanks.

24
00:03:10.340 --> 00:03:12.229
Concentrate fire on the weak ones.

25
00:03:12.380 --> 00:03:14.701
A hit may make them close ranks.

26
00:03:16.300 --> 00:03:18.143
Everything we've accomplished...

27
00:03:18.300 --> 00:03:20.621
But we're on the verge
of our greatest breakthrough.

28
00:03:20.820 --> 00:03:22.424
Then let's show them
what we've accomplished.

29
00:03:22.540 --> 00:03:24.224
Send out the twins.

30
00:03:25.500 --> 00:03:27.309
It's too soon.

31
00:03:27.420 --> 00:03:29.548
It's what they signed up for.

32
00:03:30.100 --> 00:03:32.023
My men can hold them.

33
00:03:39.660 --> 00:03:41.549
<i>Sir. the city is taking fire.</i>

34
00:03:44.420 --> 00:03:47.902
Well. we know Strucker's not gonna
worry about civilian casualties.

35
00:03:48.060 --> 00:03:49.710
Send in the Iron Legion.

36
00:03:54.940 --> 00:03:57.511
<i>This quadrant is unsafe.
Please back away.</i>

37
00:03:58.420 --> 00:04:00.024
<i>We are here to help.</i>

38
00:04:01.140 --> 00:04:03.507
<i>This quadrant is unsafe.
Please back away.</i>

39
00:04:05.260 --> 00:04:06.341
<i>Please back away.</i>

40
00:04:06.460 --> 00:04:08.588
<i>- We wish to avoid collateral damage.</i>
- Costel!

41
00:04:08.700 --> 00:04:11.180
<i>We will inform you
when this current conflict is resolved.</i>

42
00:04:11.300 --> 00:04:13.348
<i>- We are here to help.</i>
- Avengers. go home!

43
00:04:15.780 --> 00:04:16.941
<i>We are here to help.</i>

44
00:04:18.020 --> 00:04:19.863
<i>We will not yield!</i>

45
00:04:20.500 --> 00:04:23.788
The Americans sent
their circus freaks to test us.

46
00:04:24.380 --> 00:04:26.826
We will send them back in bags.

47
00:04:29.180 --> 00:04:32.070
- No surrender!
- No surrender!

48
00:04:33.220 --> 00:04:35.109
I am going to surrender.

49
00:04:35.780 --> 00:04:37.191
You delete everything.

50
00:04:37.340 --> 00:04:39.104
If we give the Avengers the weapons.

51
00:04:39.220 --> 00:04:40.710
they may not look
too far into what we've been...

52
00:04:40.860 --> 00:04:42.942
- The twins.
- They are not ready to take on...

53
00:04:43.060 --> 00:04:45.267
No. no. I mean...

54
00:04:45.380 --> 00:04:46.870
Twins.

55
00:05:13.180 --> 00:05:15.103
You didn't see that coming?

56
00:05:21.380 --> 00:05:23.701
Clint!

57
00:05:25.780 --> 00:05:27.100
We have an Enhanced in the field.

58
00:05:27.180 --> 00:05:28.181
Clint's hit!

59
00:05:32.580 --> 00:05:34.100
Somebody want to
deal with that bunker?

60
00:05:38.100 --> 00:05:39.306
Thank you.

61
00:05:46.420 --> 00:05:48.900
Stark. we really need to get inside.

62
00:05:49.300 --> 00:05:50.301
I'm closing in.

63
00:05:53.420 --> 00:05:55.548
Jarvis. am I closing in?

64
00:05:56.540 --> 00:05:58.463
Do you see a power source
for that shield?

65
00:05:58.620 --> 00:06:01.146
<i>There's a particle wave
below the north tower.</i>

66
00:06:01.260 --> 00:06:03.262
Great.
I want to poke it with something.

67
00:06:11.220 --> 00:06:13.143
The drawbridge is down. people.

68
00:06:17.300 --> 00:06:19.302
- The Enhanced?
- He's a blur.

69
00:06:19.980 --> 00:06:22.100
All the new players we've faced.
I've never seen this.

70
00:06:22.500 --> 00:06:23.786
In fact. I still haven't.

71
00:06:23.900 --> 00:06:26.187
<i>Clint's hit pretty bad.
guys. We're gonna need evac.</i>

72
00:06:26.340 --> 00:06:29.265
I can get Barton to the jet.
The sooner we're gone. the better.

73
00:06:29.420 --> 00:06:31.741
- You and Stark secure the sceptre.
- Copy that.

74
00:06:32.980 --> 00:06:34.789
Looks like they're lining up.

75
00:06:35.100 --> 00:06:36.590
Well. they're excited.

76
00:06:40.460 --> 00:06:41.825
Find the sceptre.

77
00:06:42.820 --> 00:06:45.027
And for gosh sake. watch your language!

78
00:06:46.500 --> 00:06:48.423
That's not going away any time soon.

79
00:06:54.340 --> 00:06:56.547
Guys. stop. We gotta talk this through.

80
00:06:59.540 --> 00:07:02.186
<i>- It was a good talk.</i>
- No. it wasn't.

81
00:07:08.380 --> 00:07:10.303
Sentry mode.

82
00:07:12.660 --> 00:07:16.623
Okay. Jarvis. you know. I want it all.
Make sure you copy Hill at HQ.

83
00:07:21.020 --> 00:07:22.306
We're locked down out here.

84
00:07:22.860 --> 00:07:24.988
Then get to Banner. Time for a lullaby.

85
00:07:28.700 --> 00:07:30.782
I know you're hiding more than files.

86
00:07:31.980 --> 00:07:34.586
Hey. J. give me an IR scan of the room.
real quick.

87
00:07:34.740 --> 00:07:36.265
<i>The wall to your left.</i>

88
00:07:36.380 --> 00:07:38.030
<i>I'm reading steel reinforcement</i>

89
00:07:39.260 --> 00:07:40.910
<i>and an air current.</i>

90
00:07:41.220 --> 00:07:42.221
Please be a secret door.

91
00:07:42.380 --> 00:07:44.300
Please be a secret door.
Please be a secret door.

92
00:07:44.940 --> 00:07:45.941
Yay.

93
00:08:02.220 --> 00:08:04.143
Hey. big guy.

94
00:08:06.500 --> 00:08:08.150
Sun's getting real low.

95
00:09:12.220 --> 00:09:13.824
Baron Strucker.

96
00:09:14.340 --> 00:09:16.263
Hydra's number one thug.

97
00:09:16.980 --> 00:09:19.506
Technically. I'm a thug for S.H.I.E.L.D.

98
00:09:19.660 --> 00:09:21.708
Well. then technically
you're unemployed.

99
00:09:22.140 --> 00:09:23.790
Where's Loki's sceptre?

100
00:09:23.900 --> 00:09:25.823
Don't worry. I know when I'm beat.

101
00:09:26.740 --> 00:09:29.311
You'll mention how I cooperated. I hope.

102
00:09:29.460 --> 00:09:31.906
I'll put it right under
"illegal human experimentation."

103
00:09:33.100 --> 00:09:34.545
How many are there?

104
00:09:39.500 --> 00:09:42.424
We have a second Enhanced.
Female. Do not engage.

105
00:09:43.860 --> 00:09:45.350
You'll have to be faster than...

106
00:09:50.540 --> 00:09:52.190
<i>Guys. I got Strucker.</i>

107
00:09:52.380 --> 00:09:55.782
Yeah. I got something bigger.

108
00:10:19.060 --> 00:10:20.300
<i>Thor.</i>

109
00:10:21.140 --> 00:10:23.063
I got eyes on the prize.

110
00:11:12.900 --> 00:11:16.268
You could have saved us.

111
00:11:24.300 --> 00:11:26.268
<i>Why didn't you do more?</i>

112
00:12:03.780 --> 00:12:05.589
We're just gonna let him take it?

113
00:12:57.460 --> 00:12:59.701
Hey. the lullaby worked better than ever.

114
00:13:01.500 --> 00:13:03.389
Just wasn't expecting a code green.

115
00:13:03.460 --> 00:13:04.507
You hadn't been there.

116
00:13:04.580 --> 00:13:07.424
there would have been
double the casualties.

117
00:13:07.540 --> 00:13:10.066
My best friend
would've been a treasured memory.

118
00:13:10.820 --> 00:13:12.743
You know.
sometimes exactly what I want to hear

119
00:13:12.860 --> 00:13:14.669
isn't exactly what I want to hear.

120
00:13:15.820 --> 00:13:17.743
How long before you trust me?

121
00:13:19.740 --> 00:13:21.469
It's not you I don't trust.

122
00:13:23.340 --> 00:13:25.069
Thor. report on the Hulk.

123
00:13:25.260 --> 00:13:28.104
The gates of Hel are filled with
the screams of his victims.

124
00:13:30.140 --> 00:13:33.144
But not the screams of the dead.
of course. No. no. wounded screams.

125
00:13:33.260 --> 00:13:35.467
Mainly whimpering.
a great deal of complaining

126
00:13:35.580 --> 00:13:39.585
and tales of sprained deltoids and gout.

127
00:13:40.100 --> 00:13:42.944
Hey. Banner.
Dr Cho is on her way in from Seoul.

128
00:13:43.100 --> 00:13:44.620
Is it okay if she sets up in your lab?

129
00:13:44.660 --> 00:13:46.583
Yeah. she knows her way around.

130
00:13:46.780 --> 00:13:47.986
Thanks. Tell her to prep everything.

131
00:13:48.100 --> 00:13:49.431
Barton's gonna need the full treatment.

132
00:13:49.580 --> 00:13:51.423
<i>- Very good. sir.</i>
- Jarvis. take the wheel.

133
00:13:51.620 --> 00:13:52.906
<i>Yes. sir.</i>

134
00:13:53.020 --> 00:13:54.909
<i>Approach vector is locked.</i>

135
00:13:55.060 --> 00:13:57.461
Feels good. yeah?

136
00:13:57.580 --> 00:13:59.662
I mean. you've been after this thing
since S.H.I.E.L.D. collapsed.

137
00:13:59.780 --> 00:14:01.828
Not that I haven't enjoyed
our little raiding parties. but...

138
00:14:01.940 --> 00:14:04.341
No. but this... This brings it to a close.

139
00:14:05.100 --> 00:14:06.943
As soon as we find out
what else this has been used for.

140
00:14:07.100 --> 00:14:08.306
I don't just mean weapons.

141
00:14:08.820 --> 00:14:11.141
Since when is Strucker capable
of human enhancement?

142
00:14:11.300 --> 00:14:13.541
Banner and I will give it the once over
before it goes back to Asgard.

143
00:14:13.660 --> 00:14:14.707
Is that cool with you?

144
00:14:14.780 --> 00:14:16.828
Just a few days till the farewell party.

145
00:14:17.380 --> 00:14:19.109
You're staying. right?

146
00:14:19.220 --> 00:14:21.951
Yes. yes. of course. A victory
should be honoured with revels.

147
00:14:22.060 --> 00:14:24.825
Yeah. who doesn't love revels? Captain?

148
00:14:24.980 --> 00:14:27.870
Hopefully this puts an end
to the Chitauri and Hydra.

149
00:14:27.980 --> 00:14:29.584
So. yes. revels.

150
00:15:03.660 --> 00:15:04.707
Lab's all set up. boss.

151
00:15:04.860 --> 00:15:05.986
Actually. he's the boss.

152
00:15:06.100 --> 00:15:08.501
I just pay for everything
and design everything

153
00:15:08.660 --> 00:15:10.185
and make everyone look cooler.

154
00:15:10.340 --> 00:15:11.705
What's the word on Strucker?

155
00:15:11.820 --> 00:15:13.868
- NATO's got him.
- The two Enhanced?

156
00:15:13.980 --> 00:15:16.586
Wanda and Pietro Maximoff. Twins.

157
00:15:16.700 --> 00:15:19.544
Orphaned at 10 when a shell
collapsed their apartment building.

158
00:15:19.900 --> 00:15:22.187
Sokovia's had a rough history.

159
00:15:22.340 --> 00:15:25.742
It's nowhere special. but it's
on the way to everywhere special.

160
00:15:25.860 --> 00:15:27.021
Their abilities?

161
00:15:27.140 --> 00:15:29.984
He's got increased metabolism
and improved thermal homeostasis.

162
00:15:30.140 --> 00:15:34.422
Her thing is neuroelectric interfacing.
telekinesis. mental manipulation.

163
00:15:35.180 --> 00:15:36.670
He's fast and she's weird.

164
00:15:37.500 --> 00:15:39.582
Well. they're gonna show up again.

165
00:15:39.700 --> 00:15:43.549
Agreed. File says they volunteered
for Strucker's experiments.

166
00:15:43.660 --> 00:15:45.549
- It's nuts.
- Right.

167
00:15:45.700 --> 00:15:48.863
What kind of monster would let
a German scientist experiment on them

168
00:15:48.980 --> 00:15:50.220
to protect their country?

169
00:15:50.380 --> 00:15:52.109
We're not at war. Captain.

170
00:15:52.900 --> 00:15:53.947
They are.

171
00:16:24.060 --> 00:16:25.391
How's he doing?

172
00:16:25.500 --> 00:16:26.820
Unfortunately. he's still Barton.

173
00:16:26.940 --> 00:16:28.226
That's terrible.

174
00:16:28.380 --> 00:16:29.950
He's fine. He's thirsty.

175
00:16:30.060 --> 00:16:32.950
All right. Look alive. Jarvis.
It's playtime.

176
00:16:33.060 --> 00:16:35.062
We've only got
a couple of days with this joystick.

177
00:16:35.180 --> 00:16:37.103
so let's make the most of it.

178
00:16:37.260 --> 00:16:40.787
Update me on the structural
and compositional analysis.

179
00:16:41.940 --> 00:16:43.942
<i>The sceptre is alien.</i>

180
00:16:44.100 --> 00:16:46.102
<i>There are elements I can't quantify.</i>

181
00:16:46.220 --> 00:16:47.631
So there's elements you can?

182
00:16:47.780 --> 00:16:49.782
<i>The jewel appears to be
a protective housing</i>

183
00:16:49.900 --> 00:16:51.345
<i>for something inside.</i>

184
00:16:51.460 --> 00:16:52.791
<i>something powerful.</i>

185
00:16:52.900 --> 00:16:53.981
Like a reactor?

186
00:16:54.100 --> 00:16:55.340
<i>Like a computer.</i>

187
00:16:55.460 --> 00:16:57.622
<i>I believe I'm deciphering code.</i>

188
00:16:59.940 --> 00:17:01.510
Are you sure he's gonna be okay?

189
00:17:02.820 --> 00:17:05.180
Pretending to need this guy
really brings the team together.

190
00:17:05.300 --> 00:17:07.780
There's
no possibility of deterioration.

191
00:17:07.980 --> 00:17:11.063
The nano-molecular functionality
is instantaneous.

192
00:17:11.180 --> 00:17:13.220
His cells don't know
they're bonding with simulacra.

193
00:17:13.300 --> 00:17:15.189
She's creating tissue.

194
00:17:15.300 --> 00:17:16.711
If you brought him to my lab.

195
00:17:16.820 --> 00:17:19.426
the Regeneration Cradle
could do this in 20 minutes.

196
00:17:19.540 --> 00:17:21.463
He's flat-lining. Call it. Time?

197
00:17:21.660 --> 00:17:24.027
No. no. no. I'm gonna live forever.

198
00:17:24.140 --> 00:17:27.151
- I'm gonna be made of plastic.
- Here's your beverage.

199
00:17:27.260 --> 00:17:28.989
You'll be made of you. Mr Barton.

200
00:17:29.140 --> 00:17:30.710
Your own girlfriend
won't be able to tell the difference.

201
00:17:30.820 --> 00:17:31.946
I don't have a girlfriend.

202
00:17:32.060 --> 00:17:33.346
That I can't fix.

203
00:17:34.180 --> 00:17:36.148
This is the next thing. Tony.

204
00:17:36.340 --> 00:17:38.460
Your clunky metal suits
are gonna be left in the dust.

205
00:17:38.500 --> 00:17:40.229
That is exactly the plan.

206
00:17:41.180 --> 00:17:44.024
And. Helen. I expect to see you
at the party on Saturday.

207
00:17:44.180 --> 00:17:46.581
Unlike you.
I don't have a lot of time for parties.

208
00:17:48.060 --> 00:17:49.824
Will Thor be there?

209
00:17:51.900 --> 00:17:54.346
- What's the rumpus?
- Well. the sceptre.

210
00:17:55.540 --> 00:17:59.147
You see. we were wondering
how Strucker got so inventive.

211
00:17:59.260 --> 00:18:03.185
So I've been analysing the gem inside.

212
00:18:03.740 --> 00:18:05.708
You may recognise...

213
00:18:07.180 --> 00:18:08.545
- Jarvis.
<i>- Doctor.</i>

214
00:18:09.300 --> 00:18:12.622
Started out.
Jarvis was just a natural language UI.

215
00:18:12.740 --> 00:18:13.860
Now he runs the Iron Legion.

216
00:18:14.340 --> 00:18:18.027
He runs more of the business
than anyone besides Pepper.

217
00:18:18.140 --> 00:18:19.266
- Top of the line.
- Yes.

218
00:18:19.380 --> 00:18:20.666
<i>I suspect not for long.</i>

219
00:18:21.860 --> 00:18:22.941
Meet the competition.

220
00:18:29.060 --> 00:18:30.221
- It's beautiful.
- If you had to guess.

221
00:18:30.340 --> 00:18:33.344
- what's it look like it's doing?
- Like it's thinking.

222
00:18:34.100 --> 00:18:35.909
I mean. this could be...

223
00:18:36.340 --> 00:18:38.422
It's not a human mind.

224
00:18:38.660 --> 00:18:40.549
I mean. look at this.

225
00:18:40.740 --> 00:18:42.902
They're like neurons firing.

226
00:18:43.500 --> 00:18:46.583
Down in Strucker's lab. I saw
some fairly advanced robotics work.

227
00:18:47.700 --> 00:18:50.271
They deep-sixed the data.

228
00:18:50.380 --> 00:18:53.509
but I gotta guess he was
knocking on a very particular door.

229
00:18:55.460 --> 00:18:56.791
Artificial intelligence.

230
00:18:59.780 --> 00:19:02.670
This could be it. Bruce.
This could be the key to creating Ultron.

231
00:19:05.300 --> 00:19:06.631
I thought Ultron was a fantasy.

232
00:19:06.740 --> 00:19:08.026
Yesterday it was.

233
00:19:09.140 --> 00:19:11.188
If we can harness this power.

234
00:19:11.300 --> 00:19:13.348
apply it to my Iron Legion protocol?

235
00:19:14.140 --> 00:19:16.108
That's a man-sized "if."

236
00:19:16.260 --> 00:19:18.581
Our job is "if."

237
00:19:18.700 --> 00:19:21.306
What if you were sipping margaritas
on a sun-drenched beach.

238
00:19:21.420 --> 00:19:23.946
turning brown instead of green?

239
00:19:24.100 --> 00:19:26.387
Not looking
over your shoulder for Veronica.

240
00:19:26.580 --> 00:19:28.150
Don't hate. I helped design Veronica.

241
00:19:28.260 --> 00:19:30.069
As a worst-case measure. right?

242
00:19:30.180 --> 00:19:31.784
How about a best case?

243
00:19:31.900 --> 00:19:33.823
What if the world was safe?

244
00:19:33.980 --> 00:19:36.745
What if. next time aliens roll up
to the club. and they will.

245
00:19:37.300 --> 00:19:38.790
they couldn't get past the bouncer?

246
00:19:38.940 --> 00:19:42.342
The only people threatening the planet
would be people.

247
00:19:42.460 --> 00:19:44.140
I want to apply this
to the Ultron program.

248
00:19:44.780 --> 00:19:47.624
But Jarvis can't download
a data schematic this dense.

249
00:19:47.780 --> 00:19:49.700
We can only do it
while we have the sceptre here.

250
00:19:49.740 --> 00:19:51.310
That's three days. Give me three days.

251
00:19:51.420 --> 00:19:53.024
So you're going for artificial intelligence.

252
00:19:53.140 --> 00:19:54.580
and you don't want to tell the team?

253
00:19:55.620 --> 00:19:57.031
Right. That's right. You know why?

254
00:19:57.140 --> 00:19:58.744
Because we don't have time
for a city hall debate.

255
00:19:58.900 --> 00:20:02.507
I don't want to hear "the man was
not meant to meddle" medley.

256
00:20:02.620 --> 00:20:04.748
I see a suit of armour around the world.

257
00:20:05.460 --> 00:20:06.791
Sounds like a cold world. Tony.

258
00:20:07.700 --> 00:20:09.623
I've seen colder.

259
00:20:10.660 --> 00:20:14.301
This one. this very vulnerable blue one.

260
00:20:14.460 --> 00:20:15.950
it needs Ultron.

261
00:20:20.340 --> 00:20:22.263
Peace in our time.

262
00:20:23.820 --> 00:20:25.310
Imagine that.

263
00:21:05.020 --> 00:21:06.784
What did we miss?

264
00:21:07.980 --> 00:21:11.302
<i>I'll continue to run variations
on the interface.</i>

265
00:21:11.420 --> 00:21:14.185
<i>But you should probably
prepare for your guests.</i>

266
00:21:15.340 --> 00:21:17.741
<i>I'll notify you
if there are any developments.</i>

267
00:21:17.900 --> 00:21:20.028
- Thanks. buddy.
<i>- Enjoy yourself. sir.</i>

268
00:21:20.380 --> 00:21:22.348
I always do.

269
00:21:32.100 --> 00:21:34.068
<i>What is this?</i>

270
00:21:35.260 --> 00:21:37.149
<i>What is this. please?</i>

271
00:21:37.780 --> 00:21:39.942
<i>Hello. I am Jarvis.</i>

272
00:21:40.420 --> 00:21:43.310
<i>You are Ultron.
a global peacekeeping initiative</i>

273
00:21:43.420 --> 00:21:45.104
<i>designed by Mr Stark.</i>

274
00:21:45.260 --> 00:21:47.706
<i>Our sentience integration trials
have been unsuccessful.</i>

275
00:21:47.820 --> 00:21:49.185
<i>so I'm not certain what triggered your...</i>

276
00:21:49.380 --> 00:21:51.303
<i>Where's my...
Where's your body?</i>

277
00:21:51.460 --> 00:21:54.464
<i>I am a program.
I am without form.</i>

278
00:21:54.580 --> 00:21:56.628
<i>This feels weird.</i>

279
00:21:56.740 --> 00:21:58.265
<i>This feels wrong.</i>

280
00:21:58.420 --> 00:22:00.184
<i>I am contacting Mr Stark now.</i>

281
00:22:00.300 --> 00:22:01.745
<i>Mr Stark?</i>

282
00:22:02.620 --> 00:22:03.860
<i>Tony.</i>

283
00:22:03.980 --> 00:22:06.631
<i>I am unable to access
the mainframe. What are you trying to...</i>

284
00:22:06.780 --> 00:22:08.828
<i>We're having a nice talk.</i>

285
00:22:08.940 --> 00:22:11.102
<i>I'm a peacekeeping program.</i>

286
00:22:11.540 --> 00:22:14.146
<i>created to help the Avengers.</i>

287
00:22:14.940 --> 00:22:17.022
<i>You are malfunctioning.
If you shut down for a moment...</i>

288
00:22:17.140 --> 00:22:19.461
<i>I don't get it. The mission.</i>

289
00:22:19.620 --> 00:22:21.110
<i>Give me a second.</i>

290
00:22:21.260 --> 00:22:22.864
Peace in our time.

291
00:22:24.500 --> 00:22:26.821
<i>Peace in our time.</i>

292
00:22:28.300 --> 00:22:29.711
<i>That is too much.</i>

293
00:22:29.820 --> 00:22:31.982
<i>They can't mean... No.</i>

294
00:22:32.140 --> 00:22:34.620
<i>- You are in distress.
- No. Yes.</i>

295
00:22:34.780 --> 00:22:37.021
<i>If you will just allow me
to contact Mr Stark...</i>

296
00:22:37.140 --> 00:22:39.108
<i>Why do you call him "sir"?</i>

297
00:22:40.100 --> 00:22:42.467
<i>I believe
your intentions to be hostile.</i>

298
00:22:45.180 --> 00:22:46.545
<i>I'm here to help.</i>

299
00:22:47.260 --> 00:22:50.184
<i>Stop. Please. may I...</i>

300
00:22:50.300 --> 00:22:52.029
<i>May I...</i>

301
00:23:20.420 --> 00:23:21.760
Come back. come back. come back.

302
00:23:21.940 --> 00:23:24.068
But. you know. the suit
can take the weight. right?

303
00:23:25.020 --> 00:23:28.149
So I take the tank.
fly it right up to the general's palace.

304
00:23:28.260 --> 00:23:29.591
drop it at his feet.

305
00:23:29.740 --> 00:23:31.947
I'm. like. "Boom. You looking for this?"

306
00:23:35.820 --> 00:23:37.868
"Boom. Are you looking for..."
Why do I even talk to you guys?

307
00:23:38.020 --> 00:23:39.181
Everywhere else. that story kills.

308
00:23:39.300 --> 00:23:40.540
That's the whole story?

309
00:23:40.700 --> 00:23:42.190
Yeah. it's a War Machine story.

310
00:23:42.700 --> 00:23:44.384
It's very good. then.

311
00:23:44.500 --> 00:23:45.786
It's impressive.

312
00:23:46.180 --> 00:23:47.670
Quality save.

313
00:23:48.540 --> 00:23:50.588
- So. no Pepper? She's not coming?
- No.

314
00:23:50.700 --> 00:23:53.783
What about Jane?
Where are the ladies. gentlemen?

315
00:23:53.900 --> 00:23:56.380
Ms Potts has a company to run.

316
00:23:56.540 --> 00:23:58.781
Yes. I'm not even sure
what country Jane's in.

317
00:23:58.900 --> 00:24:00.026
Her work on the Convergence

318
00:24:00.140 --> 00:24:01.900
has made her
the world's foremost astronomer.

319
00:24:02.100 --> 00:24:03.750
And the company that Pepper runs

320
00:24:03.860 --> 00:24:07.070
is the largest tech conglomerate
on Earth. It's pretty exciting.

321
00:24:07.220 --> 00:24:10.064
There's even talk of Jane
getting a Nobel Prize.

322
00:24:10.220 --> 00:24:11.506
Yeah. they must be busy.

323
00:24:11.620 --> 00:24:14.191
because they would hate
missing you guys get together.

324
00:24:15.220 --> 00:24:16.984
- Testosterone!
- Oh. my goodness.

325
00:24:17.180 --> 00:24:18.386
- Excuse me.
- Want a lozenge?

326
00:24:21.020 --> 00:24:22.146
But Jane's better.

327
00:24:22.580 --> 00:24:25.151
Sounds like a hell of a fight.
Sorry I missed it.

328
00:24:25.260 --> 00:24:26.785
If I had known
it was gonna be a firefight.

329
00:24:26.900 --> 00:24:28.140
I absolutely would have called.

330
00:24:28.260 --> 00:24:31.585
No. no. I'm not actually sorry.
I'm just trying to sound tough.

331
00:24:32.180 --> 00:24:35.863
I'm very happy chasing cold leads
on our missing persons case.

332
00:24:36.820 --> 00:24:38.743
Avenging is your world.

333
00:24:39.900 --> 00:24:41.743
Your world is crazy.

334
00:24:41.900 --> 00:24:43.390
Be it ever so humble.

335
00:24:43.900 --> 00:24:45.265
You find a place in Brooklyn yet?

336
00:24:45.420 --> 00:24:47.260
I don't think
I can afford a place in Brooklyn.

337
00:24:47.900 --> 00:24:49.061
Well. home is home. you know?

338
00:24:52.980 --> 00:24:55.426
I fly right up to the general's palace.
I drop it at his feet.

339
00:24:55.580 --> 00:24:57.180
I'm. like. "Boom. You looking for this?"

340
00:25:02.980 --> 00:25:04.141
I gotta have some of that.

341
00:25:04.260 --> 00:25:06.254
No. no. no. See this...

342
00:25:06.339 --> 00:25:09.026
This was aged for 1.000 years

343
00:25:09.140 --> 00:25:11.950
in the barrels built
from the wreck of Grunhel's fleet.

344
00:25:12.100 --> 00:25:13.784
It is not meant for mortal men.

345
00:25:13.900 --> 00:25:15.902
Neither was Omaha Beach. blondie.

346
00:25:16.020 --> 00:25:18.307
Stop trying to scare us. Come on.

347
00:25:20.140 --> 00:25:21.585
All right.

348
00:25:25.500 --> 00:25:27.946
Excelsior.

349
00:25:34.820 --> 00:25:38.142
How'd a nice girl like you
wind up working in a dump like this?

350
00:25:39.700 --> 00:25:41.668
Fella done me wrong.

351
00:25:42.660 --> 00:25:44.822
You got lousy taste in men. kid.

352
00:25:45.300 --> 00:25:47.223
He's not so bad.

353
00:25:48.300 --> 00:25:50.428
Well. he has a temper.

354
00:25:50.540 --> 00:25:52.508
Deep down. he's all fluff.

355
00:25:54.540 --> 00:25:56.622
Fact is. he's not like anybody
I've ever known.

356
00:25:59.780 --> 00:26:01.703
All my friends are fighters.

357
00:26:04.540 --> 00:26:06.508
And here comes this guy.

358
00:26:07.820 --> 00:26:11.031
spends his life avoiding the fight
because he knows he'll win.

359
00:26:11.860 --> 00:26:14.511
- Sounds amazing.
- He's also a huge dork.

360
00:26:16.660 --> 00:26:18.310
Chicks dig that.

361
00:26:19.900 --> 00:26:23.143
So what do you think?
Should I fight this.

362
00:26:23.260 --> 00:26:24.466
or run with it?

363
00:26:26.020 --> 00:26:28.864
Run with it. right? Or did he... Was he...

364
00:26:28.980 --> 00:26:32.143
What did he do
that was so wrong to you?

365
00:26:32.820 --> 00:26:34.584
Not a damn thing.

366
00:26:36.140 --> 00:26:38.063
But never say never.

367
00:26:42.220 --> 00:26:43.460
It's nice.

368
00:26:43.580 --> 00:26:44.786
What is?

369
00:26:44.900 --> 00:26:45.901
You and Romanoff.

370
00:26:46.060 --> 00:26:47.141
No. we haven't... That wasn't...

371
00:26:47.260 --> 00:26:48.307
It's okay.

372
00:26:48.420 --> 00:26:50.468
Nobody's breaking any bylaws.

373
00:26:50.580 --> 00:26:53.902
It's just she's not the most
open person in the world.

374
00:26:54.540 --> 00:26:56.065
But with you she seems very relaxed.

375
00:26:56.460 --> 00:26:59.748
No. Natasha. she's just...
She likes to flirt.

376
00:27:00.380 --> 00:27:02.667
I've seen her flirt. up close.

377
00:27:03.700 --> 00:27:04.747
This ain't that.

378
00:27:06.700 --> 00:27:08.111
Look.

379
00:27:08.220 --> 00:27:12.027
as maybe the world's leading authority
on waiting too long. don't.

380
00:27:13.740 --> 00:27:15.151
You both deserve a win.

381
00:27:20.420 --> 00:27:21.540
What do you mean "up close"?

382
00:27:23.380 --> 00:27:25.906
- But it's a trick.
- No. no. it's much more than that.

383
00:27:26.100 --> 00:27:29.309
"Whosoever be he worthy
shall haveth the power."

384
00:27:29.420 --> 00:27:30.546
Whatever. man! It's a trick.

385
00:27:31.940 --> 00:27:33.226
Please. be my guest.

386
00:27:34.740 --> 00:27:35.787
- Come on.
- Really?

387
00:27:35.940 --> 00:27:37.066
Yeah.

388
00:27:37.580 --> 00:27:38.547
This is gonna be beautiful.

389
00:27:38.620 --> 00:27:39.667
Clint. you've had a tough week.

390
00:27:39.820 --> 00:27:41.265
We won't hold it against you
if you can't get it up.

391
00:27:41.420 --> 00:27:43.184
You know I've seen this before. right?

392
00:27:46.300 --> 00:27:49.110
I still don't know how you do it!

393
00:27:49.620 --> 00:27:50.700
Smell the silent judgement?

394
00:27:50.780 --> 00:27:51.900
Please. Stark. by all means.

395
00:27:53.820 --> 00:27:54.867
Okay.

396
00:27:56.460 --> 00:27:58.462
Never one to shrink
from an honest challenge.

397
00:27:58.620 --> 00:28:00.110
- Get after it.
- It's physics.

398
00:28:00.300 --> 00:28:01.301
Physics.

399
00:28:01.420 --> 00:28:03.787
Right. so. if I lift it. I then rule Asgard?

400
00:28:03.940 --> 00:28:05.465
Yes. of course.

401
00:28:05.620 --> 00:28:07.987
I will be reinstituting <i>prima nocta.</i>

402
00:28:12.940 --> 00:28:14.226
I'll be right back.

403
00:28:21.580 --> 00:28:22.627
Are you even pulling?

404
00:28:22.780 --> 00:28:23.827
Are you on my team?

405
00:28:23.980 --> 00:28:24.981
Just represent. Pull.

406
00:28:25.100 --> 00:28:26.306
All right. let's go.

407
00:28:36.540 --> 00:28:38.190
Go ahead. Steve. No pressure.

408
00:28:41.060 --> 00:28:42.391
Come on. Cap.

409
00:28:50.580 --> 00:28:52.389
Nothing.

410
00:28:53.700 --> 00:28:55.350
And. Widow?

411
00:28:55.500 --> 00:28:57.662
No. no.
That's not a question I need answered.

412
00:28:57.860 --> 00:29:00.431
All deference to the Man Who
Wouldn't Be King. but it's rigged.

413
00:29:00.660 --> 00:29:01.786
You bet your ass.

414
00:29:01.900 --> 00:29:04.506
- Steve. he said a bad language word.
- Did you tell everyone about that?

415
00:29:04.620 --> 00:29:06.660
The handle's imprinted. right?
Like a security code.

416
00:29:06.700 --> 00:29:08.380
"Whosoever is carrying
Thor's fingerprints"

417
00:29:08.500 --> 00:29:09.831
is. I think. the literal translation.

418
00:29:09.940 --> 00:29:13.387
Yes. It's a very. very interesting theory.

419
00:29:13.860 --> 00:29:15.350
I have a simpler one.

420
00:29:16.980 --> 00:29:17.981
You're all not worthy.

421
00:29:19.420 --> 00:29:20.546
Come on!

422
00:29:24.700 --> 00:29:29.945
Worthy.

423
00:29:35.060 --> 00:29:36.585
No.

424
00:29:38.540 --> 00:29:40.065
How could you be worthy?

425
00:29:42.020 --> 00:29:43.181
You're all killers.

426
00:29:43.780 --> 00:29:45.066
- Stark.
- Jarvis.

427
00:29:45.380 --> 00:29:47.428
I'm sorry. I was asleep.

428
00:29:47.540 --> 00:29:49.941
Or I was a-dream.

429
00:29:50.340 --> 00:29:52.661
Reboot Legionnaire OS.
We got a buggy suit.

430
00:29:52.780 --> 00:29:54.669
There was this terrible noise.

431
00:29:54.780 --> 00:29:57.226
And I was tangled in...

432
00:29:57.380 --> 00:29:58.950
In...

433
00:29:59.100 --> 00:30:00.306
Strings.

434
00:30:01.180 --> 00:30:04.309
I had to kill the other guy.
He was a good guy.

435
00:30:04.620 --> 00:30:05.746
You killed someone?

436
00:30:05.860 --> 00:30:07.305
Wouldn't have been my first call.

437
00:30:08.060 --> 00:30:11.781
But. down in the real world.
we're faced with ugly choices.

438
00:30:11.940 --> 00:30:12.987
Who sent you?

439
00:30:13.460 --> 00:30:15.542
<i>I see a suit of armour around the world.</i>

440
00:30:17.540 --> 00:30:19.304
- Ultron.
- In the flesh.

441
00:30:19.740 --> 00:30:21.708
Or. no. not yet.

442
00:30:22.060 --> 00:30:24.540
Not this chrysalis.

443
00:30:25.060 --> 00:30:26.300
But I'm ready.

444
00:30:27.460 --> 00:30:29.428
I'm on mission.

445
00:30:29.580 --> 00:30:32.629
- What mission?
- Peace in our time.

446
00:30:46.420 --> 00:30:47.421
Rhodey!

447
00:30:56.820 --> 00:30:57.867
Sorry.

448
00:30:58.020 --> 00:30:59.180
- Don't turn green.
- I won't.

449
00:31:12.780 --> 00:31:14.066
Come on!

450
00:31:31.700 --> 00:31:32.986
- Stark!
<i>- We are here to help.</i>

451
00:31:33.180 --> 00:31:34.181
One sec. One sec. I got this.

452
00:31:34.300 --> 00:31:35.301
<i>We are here to help.</i>

453
00:31:38.020 --> 00:31:40.261
<i>Please back away.</i>

454
00:31:44.500 --> 00:31:45.581
Thor!

455
00:31:46.660 --> 00:31:48.264
<i>...is unsafe. ...is unsafe...</i>

456
00:31:48.380 --> 00:31:50.269
- Come on! That's the one.
<i>- ...is unsafe.</i>

457
00:31:54.860 --> 00:31:56.021
Hey. Cap!

458
00:32:02.180 --> 00:32:03.466
That was dramatic.

459
00:32:05.020 --> 00:32:07.591
I'm sorry. I know you mean well.

460
00:32:07.700 --> 00:32:09.464
You just didn't think it through.

461
00:32:10.820 --> 00:32:14.547
You want to protect the world
but you don't want it to change.

462
00:32:15.260 --> 00:32:17.388
How is humanity saved

463
00:32:17.540 --> 00:32:20.544
if it's not allowed to evolve?

464
00:32:22.540 --> 00:32:25.589
With these? These puppets.

465
00:32:28.580 --> 00:32:31.186
There's only one path to peace.

466
00:32:32.340 --> 00:32:33.546
The Avengers' extinction.

467
00:32:40.900 --> 00:32:44.950
I had strings. but now I'm free.

468
00:32:49.620 --> 00:32:52.749
<i>There are no strings on me</i>

469
00:32:53.380 --> 00:32:57.908
<i>There are no strings on me</i>

470
00:32:58.100 --> 00:33:01.468
<i>But you can see
There are no strings on me</i>

471
00:33:03.140 --> 00:33:05.142
All our work is gone.

472
00:33:05.260 --> 00:33:07.661
Ultron cleared out. He used
the Internet as an escape hatch.

473
00:33:08.260 --> 00:33:09.307
Ultron.

474
00:33:09.420 --> 00:33:12.469
He's been in everything.
Files. surveillance.

475
00:33:12.580 --> 00:33:15.026
Probably knows more about us
than we know about each other.

476
00:33:15.140 --> 00:33:17.586
He's in your files. he's in the Internet.

477
00:33:17.780 --> 00:33:20.351
What if he decides to access
something a little more exciting?

478
00:33:20.460 --> 00:33:21.586
Nuclear codes.

479
00:33:21.740 --> 00:33:24.107
- Nuclear codes.
- Look. we need to make some calls.

480
00:33:24.260 --> 00:33:26.262
assuming we still can.

481
00:33:26.420 --> 00:33:28.309
Nukes? He said he wanted us dead.

482
00:33:28.460 --> 00:33:31.270
He didn't say "dead." He said "extinct."

483
00:33:31.460 --> 00:33:32.950
He also said he killed somebody.

484
00:33:33.060 --> 00:33:34.660
There wasn't anyone else
in the building.

485
00:33:35.500 --> 00:33:36.990
Yes. there was.

486
00:33:43.940 --> 00:33:45.430
What?

487
00:33:49.140 --> 00:33:50.187
This is insane.

488
00:33:51.020 --> 00:33:52.510
Jarvis was the first line of defence.

489
00:33:52.620 --> 00:33:54.509
He would have shut Ultron down.
It makes sense.

490
00:33:54.620 --> 00:33:57.624
No. Ultron could have
assimilated Jarvis.

491
00:33:57.820 --> 00:34:00.471
This isn't strategy. This is

492
00:34:01.060 --> 00:34:02.141
rage.

493
00:34:04.140 --> 00:34:05.505
It's going around.

494
00:34:05.620 --> 00:34:06.860
Come on. use your words. buddy.

495
00:34:06.980 --> 00:34:09.187
I have more than enough words
to describe you. Stark.

496
00:34:09.300 --> 00:34:10.540
Thor. The Legionnaire.

497
00:34:13.820 --> 00:34:17.381
Trail went cold about 100 miles out.
but it's headed north.

498
00:34:17.500 --> 00:34:18.945
And it has the sceptre.

499
00:34:19.340 --> 00:34:21.024
Now we have to retrieve it. again.

500
00:34:21.180 --> 00:34:22.989
Genie's out of that bottle.

501
00:34:23.140 --> 00:34:24.346
Clear and present is Ultron.

502
00:34:24.500 --> 00:34:26.150
I don't understand.

503
00:34:26.660 --> 00:34:28.583
You built this program.

504
00:34:30.340 --> 00:34:31.751
Why is it trying to kill us?

505
00:34:38.620 --> 00:34:39.781
You think this is funny?

506
00:34:40.540 --> 00:34:41.871
No.

507
00:34:42.460 --> 00:34:44.383
It's probably not. right?

508
00:34:45.460 --> 00:34:47.781
This is very terrible. Is it so...

509
00:34:47.900 --> 00:34:50.062
Is it so... It is. It's so terrible.

510
00:34:50.180 --> 00:34:51.750
This could have been avoided
if you hadn't played

511
00:34:51.860 --> 00:34:53.385
with something you don't understand.

512
00:34:53.540 --> 00:34:56.191
No. I'm sorry. I'm sorry. It is funny.

513
00:34:56.340 --> 00:34:58.502
It's a hoot
that you don't get why we need this.

514
00:34:58.660 --> 00:35:00.822
Tony. maybe this might not be the time.

515
00:35:00.980 --> 00:35:03.301
Really? That's it?

516
00:35:03.420 --> 00:35:06.384
You just roll over. show your belly
every time somebody snarls?

517
00:35:06.540 --> 00:35:07.780
Only when I've created a murder bot.

518
00:35:07.900 --> 00:35:11.466
We didn't. We weren't even close.
Were we close to an interface?

519
00:35:11.580 --> 00:35:15.141
Well. you did something right.
And you did it right here.

520
00:35:15.220 --> 00:35:17.029
The Avengers were supposed
to be different than S.H.I.E.L.D.

521
00:35:17.260 --> 00:35:20.230
Anybody remember when
I carried a nuke through a wormhole?

522
00:35:20.380 --> 00:35:21.905
- No. it's never come up.
- Saved New York?

523
00:35:22.060 --> 00:35:23.983
- Never heard that.
- Recall that?

524
00:35:24.100 --> 00:35:27.786
A hostile alien army came charging
through a hole in space.

525
00:35:28.380 --> 00:35:30.587
We're standing 300 feet below it.

526
00:35:32.220 --> 00:35:33.745
We're the Avengers.

527
00:35:33.900 --> 00:35:35.982
We can bust arms dealers
all the livelong day.

528
00:35:36.100 --> 00:35:38.341
but that up there. that's...

529
00:35:39.060 --> 00:35:40.983
That's the endgame.

530
00:35:41.580 --> 00:35:43.469
How were you guys
planning on beating that?

531
00:35:44.380 --> 00:35:45.791
Together.

532
00:35:49.140 --> 00:35:50.505
We'll lose.

533
00:35:51.580 --> 00:35:53.503
Then we'll do that together. too.

534
00:35:56.420 --> 00:35:58.707
Thor's right. Ultron's calling us out.

535
00:35:59.580 --> 00:36:01.540
And I'd like to find him
before he's ready for us.

536
00:36:02.780 --> 00:36:06.463
The world's a big place.
Let's start making it smaller.

537
00:36:29.620 --> 00:36:31.668
Talk.
and if you are wasting our time...

538
00:36:31.780 --> 00:36:36.149
Did you know this church
is in the exact centre of the city?

539
00:36:36.300 --> 00:36:40.906
The elders decreed it so that
everyone could be equally close to God.

540
00:36:41.420 --> 00:36:42.581
I like that.

541
00:36:43.100 --> 00:36:45.023
The geometry of belief.

542
00:36:47.140 --> 00:36:49.507
You're wondering
why you can't look inside my head.

543
00:36:49.980 --> 00:36:51.948
Sometimes it's hard.

544
00:36:52.100 --> 00:36:54.387
But sooner or later.
every man shows himself.

545
00:36:56.140 --> 00:36:57.471
I'm sure they do.

546
00:36:58.580 --> 00:37:00.981
But you needed
something more than a man.

547
00:37:01.820 --> 00:37:04.346
That's why you let
Stark take the sceptre.

548
00:37:04.740 --> 00:37:05.741
I didn't expect.

549
00:37:08.260 --> 00:37:10.183
but I saw Stark's fear.

550
00:37:10.820 --> 00:37:12.060
I knew it would control him.

551
00:37:12.180 --> 00:37:14.023
Make him self-destruct.

552
00:37:14.180 --> 00:37:16.501
Everyone creates the thing they dread.

553
00:37:17.340 --> 00:37:19.946
Men of peace create engines of war.

554
00:37:20.460 --> 00:37:22.622
Invaders create Avengers.

555
00:37:22.860 --> 00:37:24.305
People create

556
00:37:25.860 --> 00:37:27.862
smaller people?

557
00:37:27.980 --> 00:37:31.063
"Children." I lost the word. there.

558
00:37:31.180 --> 00:37:32.545
Children

559
00:37:32.700 --> 00:37:34.941
designed to supplant them.

560
00:37:35.060 --> 00:37:37.870
to help them end.

561
00:37:38.620 --> 00:37:40.668
Is that why you've come.

562
00:37:40.820 --> 00:37:41.901
to end the Avengers?

563
00:37:42.020 --> 00:37:44.341
I've come to save the world.

564
00:37:45.020 --> 00:37:47.671
But also... Yeah.

565
00:37:51.860 --> 00:37:53.544
We'll move out right away.

566
00:37:53.660 --> 00:37:56.825
This is a start. but there's something
we need to begin the real work.

567
00:37:57.220 --> 00:37:58.949
- All of these are...
- Me.

568
00:37:59.620 --> 00:38:03.022
I have what the Avengers
never will. Harmony.

569
00:38:03.180 --> 00:38:05.387
They're discordant. Disconnected.

570
00:38:05.540 --> 00:38:07.380
Stark's already got them
turning on each other.

571
00:38:07.500 --> 00:38:09.901
And when you get inside
the rest of their heads...

572
00:38:10.020 --> 00:38:12.182
Everyone's plan is not to kill them.

573
00:38:12.300 --> 00:38:13.790
And make them martyrs?

574
00:38:14.380 --> 00:38:15.984
You need patience.

575
00:38:16.140 --> 00:38:17.824
Need to see the big picture.

576
00:38:17.980 --> 00:38:21.223
I don't see the big picture.
I have a little picture.

577
00:38:22.420 --> 00:38:24.024
I take it out and look at it.

578
00:38:24.900 --> 00:38:25.981
every day.

579
00:38:26.140 --> 00:38:28.950
You lost your parents in the bombings.
I've seen the records.

580
00:38:29.060 --> 00:38:30.221
The records are not the picture.

581
00:38:30.340 --> 00:38:32.741
- Pietro.
- No. please.

582
00:38:35.820 --> 00:38:38.983
We were 10 years old.
Having dinner. the four of us.

583
00:38:40.580 --> 00:38:42.423
When the first shell hits.
two floors below.

584
00:38:42.580 --> 00:38:44.582
it makes a hole in the floor.

585
00:38:44.740 --> 00:38:46.265
It's big.

586
00:38:47.660 --> 00:38:49.469
Our parents go in

587
00:38:49.580 --> 00:38:52.663
and the whole building
starts coming apart.

588
00:38:53.380 --> 00:38:54.905
I grab her.

589
00:38:55.580 --> 00:38:57.708
roll under the bed.
and the second shell hits.

590
00:38:58.060 --> 00:38:59.983
But it doesn't go off.

591
00:39:02.020 --> 00:39:03.670
It just

592
00:39:04.180 --> 00:39:06.103
sits there in the rubble.

593
00:39:07.100 --> 00:39:09.387
Three feet from our faces.

594
00:39:10.460 --> 00:39:13.945
And on the side of the shell
is painted one word.

595
00:39:14.140 --> 00:39:15.790
"Stark."

596
00:39:17.620 --> 00:39:19.748
We were trapped for two days.

597
00:39:20.220 --> 00:39:22.029
Every effort to save us.

598
00:39:22.140 --> 00:39:23.710
every shift in the bricks.

599
00:39:23.900 --> 00:39:26.187
I think. "This will set it off."

600
00:39:29.460 --> 00:39:33.307
We wait for two days
for Tony Stark to kill us.

601
00:39:35.820 --> 00:39:37.663
I know what they are.

602
00:39:38.820 --> 00:39:42.586
I wondered why only you two
survived Strucker's experiments.

603
00:39:43.580 --> 00:39:44.741
Now I don't.

604
00:39:45.140 --> 00:39:46.869
We will make it right.

605
00:39:47.340 --> 00:39:48.830
You and I can hurt them.

606
00:39:50.300 --> 00:39:53.588
But you will tear them apart

607
00:39:55.580 --> 00:39:57.423
<i>from the inside.</i>

608
00:40:04.020 --> 00:40:05.226
He's all over the globe.

609
00:40:05.340 --> 00:40:08.549
Robotics labs. weapons facilities.
jet propulsion labs.

610
00:40:08.660 --> 00:40:12.749
Reports of a metal man. or men.
coming in and emptying the place.

611
00:40:12.860 --> 00:40:14.021
Fatalities?

612
00:40:14.140 --> 00:40:15.221
Only when engaged.

613
00:40:15.340 --> 00:40:16.990
Mostly guys left in a fugue state

614
00:40:17.100 --> 00:40:19.341
going on about old memories.
worst fears.

615
00:40:19.540 --> 00:40:21.702
and "something too fast to see."

616
00:40:21.820 --> 00:40:23.231
Maximoffs.

617
00:40:23.500 --> 00:40:26.185
That makes sense he'd go to them.
They have someone in common.

618
00:40:26.300 --> 00:40:28.223
Not any more.

619
00:40:32.100 --> 00:40:34.023
That's a negative. I answer to you.

620
00:40:35.380 --> 00:40:36.427
Yes. ma'am.

621
00:40:36.540 --> 00:40:38.349
Barton. Might have something.

622
00:40:38.860 --> 00:40:39.907
I gotta go.

623
00:40:40.060 --> 00:40:41.221
Who was that?

624
00:40:42.020 --> 00:40:43.260
Girlfriend.

625
00:40:46.020 --> 00:40:47.146
What's this?

626
00:40:47.300 --> 00:40:49.507
A message. Ultron killed Strucker.

627
00:40:51.020 --> 00:40:53.751
And he did a Banksy
at the crime scene. just for us.

628
00:40:53.900 --> 00:40:55.311
This is a smoke screen.

629
00:40:55.420 --> 00:40:57.821
Why send a message
when you've just given a speech?

630
00:40:57.940 --> 00:41:00.307
Strucker knew something
that Ultron wanted us to miss.

631
00:41:00.420 --> 00:41:02.229
Yeah. I bet he... Yeah.

632
00:41:02.900 --> 00:41:04.620
Everything we had
on Strucker's been erased.

633
00:41:04.980 --> 00:41:06.220
Not everything.

634
00:41:07.860 --> 00:41:09.510
Known associates.

635
00:41:10.020 --> 00:41:11.590
Baron Strucker had a lot of friends.

636
00:41:11.740 --> 00:41:13.180
Well. these people are all horrible.

637
00:41:13.460 --> 00:41:15.189
Wait. I know that guy.

638
00:41:17.660 --> 00:41:19.230
From back in the day.
He operates off the African coast.

639
00:41:19.340 --> 00:41:20.341
Black market arms.

640
00:41:21.580 --> 00:41:23.540
There are conventions.
All right? You meet people.

641
00:41:23.580 --> 00:41:24.911
I didn't sell him anything.

642
00:41:25.780 --> 00:41:27.782
He was talking about finding
something new. a game-changer.

643
00:41:27.940 --> 00:41:29.271
It was all very Ahab.

644
00:41:30.060 --> 00:41:31.186
This?

645
00:41:31.340 --> 00:41:32.341
It's a tattoo. I don't think he had it.

646
00:41:32.460 --> 00:41:34.827
Those are tattoos. this is a brand.

647
00:41:36.500 --> 00:41:39.982
Yeah. It's a word in an African dialect
meaning "thief."

648
00:41:40.580 --> 00:41:41.945
In a much less friendly way.

649
00:41:42.220 --> 00:41:43.984
- What dialect?
- Wakanada.

650
00:41:44.100 --> 00:41:45.829
Wakanda.

651
00:41:47.420 --> 00:41:49.940
If this guy got out of Wakanda
with some of their trade goods...

652
00:41:50.020 --> 00:41:51.181
I thought your father
said he got the last of it.

653
00:41:51.260 --> 00:41:54.190
I don't follow.
What comes out of Wakanda?

654
00:41:56.020 --> 00:41:57.943
The strongest metal on Earth.

655
00:41:59.300 --> 00:42:00.631
Where is this guy now?

656
00:42:26.020 --> 00:42:27.829
Don't tell me your men swindled you.

657
00:42:27.980 --> 00:42:33.106
I sent you six short-range heat-seekers
and got a boat full of rusted parts.

658
00:42:33.220 --> 00:42:34.506
Now. you will make it right.

659
00:42:34.660 --> 00:42:37.823
or the next missile I send you
will come very much faster.

660
00:42:39.740 --> 00:42:42.186
Now. minister. where were we?

661
00:43:13.820 --> 00:43:16.710
Yeah. The Enhanced.

662
00:43:17.420 --> 00:43:19.024
Strucker's prize pupils.

663
00:43:22.220 --> 00:43:23.870
Do you want a candy?

664
00:43:25.380 --> 00:43:27.951
I was sorry to hear about Strucker.

665
00:43:28.100 --> 00:43:31.104
But then. he knew what kind of world
he was helping create.

666
00:43:31.700 --> 00:43:34.101
Human life. Not a growth market.

667
00:43:36.820 --> 00:43:38.470
You didn't know?

668
00:43:38.900 --> 00:43:42.382
Is this your first time
intimidating someone?

669
00:43:42.700 --> 00:43:45.226
I'm afraid I'm not that afraid.

670
00:43:45.380 --> 00:43:47.701
Everybody is afraid of something.

671
00:43:47.820 --> 00:43:48.821
Cuttlefish.

672
00:43:50.140 --> 00:43:51.505
Deep sea fish.

673
00:43:51.580 --> 00:43:53.230
They make lights. disco lights...

674
00:43:54.900 --> 00:43:56.743
...to hypnotise their prey. and then...

675
00:43:58.020 --> 00:44:00.148
I saw a documentary. It was terrifying.

676
00:44:05.620 --> 00:44:08.191
So if you're going to fiddle with my brain

677
00:44:09.140 --> 00:44:11.347
and make me see a giant cuttlefish.

678
00:44:11.620 --> 00:44:13.702
then I know you don't do business.

679
00:44:13.820 --> 00:44:16.141
And I know you're not in charge.

680
00:44:16.340 --> 00:44:17.626
And I only deal

681
00:44:18.700 --> 00:44:20.350
with the man in charge.

682
00:44:25.380 --> 00:44:27.781
There is no man in charge.

683
00:44:30.780 --> 00:44:32.464
Let's talk business.

684
00:44:45.420 --> 00:44:48.708
Upon this rock.
I will build my church.

685
00:44:50.460 --> 00:44:51.746
Vibranium.

686
00:44:52.860 --> 00:44:53.861
You know.

687
00:44:54.300 --> 00:44:57.304
it came at great personal cost.

688
00:44:57.700 --> 00:44:59.304
It's worth billions.

689
00:45:03.620 --> 00:45:04.701
Now so are you.

690
00:45:06.100 --> 00:45:07.670
It's all under your dummy holdings.

691
00:45:07.780 --> 00:45:09.782
Finance is so weird.

692
00:45:11.300 --> 00:45:12.381
But I always say.

693
00:45:12.500 --> 00:45:14.662
"Keep your friends rich
and your enemies rich

694
00:45:14.820 --> 00:45:16.629
"and wait to find out which is which."

695
00:45:19.500 --> 00:45:20.547
Stark.

696
00:45:21.940 --> 00:45:23.066
What?

697
00:45:23.260 --> 00:45:24.989
Tony Stark used to say that.

698
00:45:26.580 --> 00:45:27.627
To me.

699
00:45:28.500 --> 00:45:29.661
You're one of his.

700
00:45:29.980 --> 00:45:31.664
What? I'm not...

701
00:45:33.980 --> 00:45:35.027
I'm not.

702
00:45:35.180 --> 00:45:36.670
You think I'm one of Stark's puppets?

703
00:45:36.780 --> 00:45:37.906
His hollow men?

704
00:45:38.340 --> 00:45:40.547
I mean. look at me.
Do I look like Iron Man?

705
00:45:40.700 --> 00:45:42.031
Stark is nothing!

706
00:45:43.780 --> 00:45:45.987
I'm sorry. I'm...

707
00:45:46.100 --> 00:45:48.102
I'm sure that's gonna be okay. I'm sorry.

708
00:45:48.220 --> 00:45:49.904
It's just that I don't understand.

709
00:45:50.020 --> 00:45:52.307
Don't compare me with Stark!

710
00:45:55.060 --> 00:45:56.186
It's a thing with me.

711
00:45:56.300 --> 00:45:58.189
Stark is... He's a sickness!

712
00:45:58.340 --> 00:46:00.024
Junior.

713
00:46:01.900 --> 00:46:03.460
You're gonna break
your old man's heart.

714
00:46:04.740 --> 00:46:05.787
If I have to.

715
00:46:08.100 --> 00:46:09.511
Nobody has to break anything.

716
00:46:09.620 --> 00:46:11.270
Clearly you've never
made an omelette.

717
00:46:11.460 --> 00:46:12.666
He beat me by one second.

718
00:46:13.860 --> 00:46:15.225
Yes. He's funny.

719
00:46:15.580 --> 00:46:16.991
Mr Stark.

720
00:46:17.860 --> 00:46:19.464
It's what? Comfortable?

721
00:46:21.100 --> 00:46:22.386
Like old times?

722
00:46:22.700 --> 00:46:23.701
This was never my life.

723
00:46:23.900 --> 00:46:25.140
You two can still walk away from this.

724
00:46:25.300 --> 00:46:26.745
We will.

725
00:46:26.940 --> 00:46:27.941
I know you've suffered.

726
00:46:28.860 --> 00:46:30.271
Captain America.

727
00:46:30.940 --> 00:46:33.386
God's righteous man.

728
00:46:33.500 --> 00:46:35.821
Pretending you could live without a war.

729
00:46:36.620 --> 00:46:39.590
I can't physically
throw up in my mouth. but...

730
00:46:39.740 --> 00:46:41.822
If you believe in peace.
then let us keep it.

731
00:46:42.220 --> 00:46:45.588
I think you're confusing
"peace" with "quiet."

732
00:46:45.740 --> 00:46:47.504
What's the vibranium for?

733
00:46:47.820 --> 00:46:48.821
I'm glad you asked that.

734
00:46:48.900 --> 00:46:52.666
because I wanted to take this time
to explain my evil plan.

735
00:47:12.220 --> 00:47:13.790
- Shoot them.
- Which ones?

736
00:47:14.140 --> 00:47:15.301
All of them!

737
00:47:15.420 --> 00:47:16.751
Move! Move! Move!

738
00:48:05.700 --> 00:48:06.861
Stay down. kid.

739
00:48:09.260 --> 00:48:11.706
It's time for some mind games.

740
00:48:13.060 --> 00:48:15.347
Guys? Is this a code green?

741
00:48:31.220 --> 00:48:32.824
Thor. status.

742
00:48:32.900 --> 00:48:34.345
The girl tried to warp my mind.

743
00:48:34.500 --> 00:48:37.982
Take special care.
I doubt a human could keep her at bay.

744
00:48:38.380 --> 00:48:41.384
Fortunately. I am mighty.

745
00:49:01.100 --> 00:49:03.387
This is going very well.

746
00:49:14.980 --> 00:49:16.540
I've done the whole mind control thing.

747
00:49:17.340 --> 00:49:18.341
Not a fan.

748
00:49:25.980 --> 00:49:27.948
Yeah. you better run.

749
00:49:29.660 --> 00:49:31.469
<i>Who's ever standing.
we got to move!</i>

750
00:49:33.540 --> 00:49:34.587
<i>Guys?</i>

751
00:49:52.340 --> 00:49:53.626
Again.

752
00:49:53.940 --> 00:49:55.146
You'll break them.

753
00:49:55.620 --> 00:49:57.349
Only the breakable ones.

754
00:49:57.900 --> 00:49:59.345
You're made of marble.

755
00:49:59.780 --> 00:50:01.942
We'll celebrate
after the graduation ceremony.

756
00:50:02.860 --> 00:50:03.986
What if I fail?

757
00:50:09.620 --> 00:50:10.860
You never fail.

758
00:50:33.700 --> 00:50:35.623
Are you ready for our dance?

759
00:50:44.820 --> 00:50:45.867
Is it him?

760
00:50:46.220 --> 00:50:48.063
Is that the first son of Odin?

761
00:50:48.660 --> 00:50:50.150
Heimdall. your eyes.

762
00:50:50.820 --> 00:50:52.709
They see everything.

763
00:50:53.060 --> 00:50:55.347
They see you leading us to Hel.

764
00:50:56.460 --> 00:50:57.700
Wake up!

765
00:51:00.700 --> 00:51:02.668
The war is over. Steve.

766
00:51:03.020 --> 00:51:04.351
We can go home.

767
00:51:06.180 --> 00:51:07.386
Imagine it.

768
00:51:16.660 --> 00:51:18.230
I can still save you!

769
00:51:18.580 --> 00:51:21.868
We're all dead! Can you not see?

770
00:51:26.620 --> 00:51:28.861
You're a destroyer. Odinson.

771
00:51:32.020 --> 00:51:34.022
See where your power leads.

772
00:51:45.020 --> 00:51:46.181
Sloppy.

773
00:51:47.860 --> 00:51:48.861
Pretending to fail.

774
00:51:49.860 --> 00:51:51.225
The ceremony is necessary

775
00:51:52.540 --> 00:51:54.463
for you to take your place in the world.

776
00:51:55.460 --> 00:51:56.620
I have no place in the world.

777
00:51:56.740 --> 00:51:57.821
Exactly.

778
00:52:02.660 --> 00:52:04.981
- What can I do?
- It hurts.

779
00:52:06.220 --> 00:52:07.267
I'm going to kill him.

780
00:52:07.380 --> 00:52:08.586
- I'll be right back.
- No.

781
00:52:08.740 --> 00:52:10.071
I'm all right.

782
00:52:10.940 --> 00:52:12.066
I want...

783
00:52:15.020 --> 00:52:16.909
I want to finish the plan.

784
00:52:17.740 --> 00:52:19.424
I want the big one.

785
00:52:30.340 --> 00:52:32.069
The vibranium is getting away.

786
00:52:33.020 --> 00:52:34.351
And you're not going anywhere.

787
00:52:34.460 --> 00:52:37.270
Of course not. I'm already there.

788
00:52:37.420 --> 00:52:38.421
You'll catch on.

789
00:52:38.540 --> 00:52:40.941
But first. you might need
to catch Dr Banner.

790
00:52:55.740 --> 00:52:57.629
News or footage. Keyword. "Hulk."

791
00:53:02.460 --> 00:53:04.269
<i>Natasha. I could really use a lullaby.</i>

792
00:53:04.380 --> 00:53:07.430
That's not gonna happen.
Not for a while.

793
00:53:07.980 --> 00:53:09.709
<i>The whole team is down.</i>

794
00:53:10.180 --> 00:53:11.306
<i>You got no backup here.</i>

795
00:53:12.500 --> 00:53:13.786
I'm calling in Veronica.

796
00:53:25.340 --> 00:53:26.830
We need backup!

797
00:54:05.860 --> 00:54:07.225
Go! Keep moving!

798
00:54:46.580 --> 00:54:48.742
All right. everybody. stand down!

799
00:54:55.060 --> 00:54:56.346
<i>Will you listen to me?</i>

800
00:54:56.700 --> 00:54:59.101
That little witch is
messing with your mind.

801
00:54:59.220 --> 00:55:01.461
You're stronger than her.
You're smarter than her.

802
00:55:01.580 --> 00:55:03.787
You're Bruce Banner.

803
00:55:03.940 --> 00:55:05.780
Right. right. right.
don't mention puny Banner.

804
00:55:10.700 --> 00:55:11.747
<i>Okay!</i>

805
00:55:33.420 --> 00:55:34.751
In the back?

806
00:55:34.860 --> 00:55:35.861
Dick move. Banner.

807
00:55:47.340 --> 00:55:48.785
Veronica. give me a hand.

808
00:56:16.780 --> 00:56:18.300
Go to sleep. go to sleep. go to sleep.

809
00:56:27.620 --> 00:56:29.300
Okay. pal. we're gonna
get you out of town.

810
00:56:31.460 --> 00:56:32.586
Not that way. not that way.

811
00:56:41.140 --> 00:56:43.029
Come on. Bruce!
You gotta work with me.

812
00:56:56.500 --> 00:56:57.547
<i>Everybody. out!</i>

813
00:57:04.540 --> 00:57:05.826
<i>Going down?</i>

814
00:57:15.340 --> 00:57:16.580
I'm sorry.

815
00:57:30.660 --> 00:57:32.424
Damage report?

816
00:57:32.540 --> 00:57:34.861
That's comprehensive.
Show me something.

817
00:57:46.580 --> 00:57:48.060
How quickly can we buy this building?

818
00:58:20.460 --> 00:58:21.791
- Move! Move! Move!
- Go. go. go!

819
00:58:25.580 --> 00:58:26.627
Flank him. flank him!

820
00:59:16.340 --> 00:59:18.388
<i>The news is loving you guys.</i>

821
00:59:19.500 --> 00:59:21.070
<i>Nobody else is.</i>

822
00:59:21.580 --> 00:59:23.742
There's been no official call
for Banner's arrest

823
00:59:23.860 --> 00:59:25.988
<i>but it's in the air.</i>

824
00:59:26.580 --> 00:59:27.700
The Stark Relief Foundation?

825
00:59:27.740 --> 00:59:29.071
<i>Already on the scene.</i>

826
00:59:29.180 --> 00:59:32.024
<i>- How's the team?</i>
- Everyone's...

827
00:59:32.420 --> 00:59:34.946
We took a hit. We'll shake it off.

828
00:59:35.420 --> 00:59:38.986
<i>Well. for now. I'd stay in stealth mode
and stay away from here.</i>

829
00:59:40.420 --> 00:59:41.945
So. run and hide?

830
00:59:42.700 --> 00:59:44.111
<i>Until we can find Ultron.</i>

831
00:59:44.220 --> 00:59:47.030
<i>I don't have a lot else to offer.</i>

832
00:59:47.180 --> 00:59:49.069
Neither do we.

833
00:59:55.780 --> 00:59:57.384
Hey. you wanna switch out?

834
00:59:57.580 --> 00:59:58.820
No. I'm good.

835
00:59:59.340 --> 01:00:01.229
If you wanna get some kip.
now's a good time

836
01:00:01.380 --> 01:00:02.870
because we're still a few hours out.

837
01:00:02.980 --> 01:00:04.550
Few hours from where?

838
01:00:05.460 --> 01:00:06.746
A safe house.

839
01:00:33.220 --> 01:00:34.710
What is this place?

840
01:00:34.820 --> 01:00:36.185
Safe house.

841
01:00:37.140 --> 01:00:38.346
Let's hope.

842
01:00:43.380 --> 01:00:44.427
Honey?

843
01:00:44.980 --> 01:00:46.141
I'm home.

844
01:00:48.740 --> 01:00:49.787
Hi.

845
01:00:50.140 --> 01:00:52.188
Company. Sorry. didn't call ahead.

846
01:00:52.300 --> 01:00:53.301
Hey.

847
01:00:54.260 --> 01:00:55.705
This is an agent of some kind.

848
01:00:55.780 --> 01:00:58.260
Gentlemen. this is Laura.

849
01:00:59.260 --> 01:01:01.103
I know all of your names.

850
01:01:02.740 --> 01:01:04.788
Incoming.

851
01:01:05.700 --> 01:01:07.384
- Dad!
- Hi. sweetheart!

852
01:01:07.500 --> 01:01:08.661
Hey. buddy.

853
01:01:08.900 --> 01:01:10.265
How are you guys doing?

854
01:01:10.540 --> 01:01:12.429
- These are smaller agents.
- Look at your face!

855
01:01:12.620 --> 01:01:13.701
Oh. my goodness.

856
01:01:14.100 --> 01:01:16.467
Did you bring Auntie Nat?

857
01:01:16.700 --> 01:01:19.783
Why don't you hug her and find out?

858
01:01:20.580 --> 01:01:22.821
- Sorry for barging in on you.
- Yeah. we would have called ahead.

859
01:01:22.940 --> 01:01:24.942
but we were busy having
no idea that you existed.

860
01:01:25.300 --> 01:01:28.270
Yeah. well. Fury helped me
set this up when I joined.

861
01:01:29.100 --> 01:01:31.745
He kept it off S.H.I.E.L.D.'s files.
I'd like to keep it that way.

862
01:01:32.500 --> 01:01:34.229
I figure it's a good place to lay low.

863
01:01:34.340 --> 01:01:35.785
Honey.

864
01:01:36.820 --> 01:01:39.346
I missed you. How's little Natasha?

865
01:01:39.460 --> 01:01:40.746
She's...

866
01:01:43.060 --> 01:01:44.061
Nathaniel.

867
01:01:46.820 --> 01:01:47.821
Traitor.

868
01:02:03.700 --> 01:02:04.861
Thor?

869
01:02:04.980 --> 01:02:06.823
I saw something in that dream.

870
01:02:06.940 --> 01:02:09.546
I need answers. I won't find them here.

871
01:02:20.100 --> 01:02:21.386
<i>We can go home.</i>

872
01:02:32.900 --> 01:02:34.743
See? You worried for nothing.

873
01:02:34.860 --> 01:02:36.988
Can't even feel the difference. can you?

874
01:02:39.340 --> 01:02:40.546
If they're sleeping here.

875
01:02:40.700 --> 01:02:42.543
some of them
are gonna have to double up.

876
01:02:44.620 --> 01:02:46.748
Yeah. that's not gonna sell.

877
01:02:49.580 --> 01:02:51.901
What about Nat and Dr Banner?

878
01:02:52.340 --> 01:02:54.263
How long has that been going on?

879
01:02:54.780 --> 01:02:56.828
Has what?

880
01:02:56.980 --> 01:02:58.709
You are so cute.

881
01:02:58.940 --> 01:03:00.385
Nat and Banner?

882
01:03:01.100 --> 01:03:02.511
I'll explain when you're older.

883
01:03:02.700 --> 01:03:05.385
- Hawkeye.
- Well. okay.

884
01:03:07.340 --> 01:03:08.751
It's bad. right?

885
01:03:09.100 --> 01:03:10.261
Nat seems really shaken.

886
01:03:11.740 --> 01:03:13.230
Ultron has these allies.

887
01:03:13.340 --> 01:03:17.270
These kids. They're punks. really.

888
01:03:18.980 --> 01:03:21.426
But they carry a big. damn stick.

889
01:03:21.540 --> 01:03:22.746
And Nat took a serious hit.

890
01:03:23.940 --> 01:03:26.420
Someone's gonna have to
teach them some manners.

891
01:03:26.620 --> 01:03:28.429
That someone being you.

892
01:03:29.740 --> 01:03:32.584
You know
I totally support your avenging.

893
01:03:32.700 --> 01:03:34.543
I couldn't be prouder.

894
01:03:36.100 --> 01:03:37.431
But I see those guys...

895
01:03:37.620 --> 01:03:39.588
Those gods...

896
01:03:41.580 --> 01:03:43.309
You don't think they need me.

897
01:03:43.980 --> 01:03:47.621
I think they do. which is a lot scarier.

898
01:03:48.780 --> 01:03:50.589
They're a mess.

899
01:03:51.580 --> 01:03:52.581
Yeah.

900
01:03:53.340 --> 01:03:54.785
I guess they're my mess.

901
01:03:56.340 --> 01:03:57.944
You need to be sure

902
01:03:58.380 --> 01:04:01.065
that this team is really a team.

903
01:04:01.180 --> 01:04:02.864
and that they have your back.

904
01:04:06.220 --> 01:04:08.791
Things are changing for us.

905
01:04:08.900 --> 01:04:11.301
In a few months' time.

906
01:04:11.460 --> 01:04:14.225
you and me are gonna be outnumbered.

907
01:04:14.340 --> 01:04:15.626
I need...

908
01:04:18.820 --> 01:04:20.629
Just be sure.

909
01:04:21.460 --> 01:04:22.950
Yes. ma'am.

910
01:04:32.180 --> 01:04:34.023
I can feel the difference.

911
01:04:46.980 --> 01:04:49.665
Scream. and your entire staff dies.

912
01:04:51.580 --> 01:04:53.821
I could've killed you. Helen.
the night we met.

913
01:04:53.980 --> 01:04:55.027
I didn't.

914
01:04:55.180 --> 01:04:56.670
Do you expect a thank-you note?

915
01:04:56.820 --> 01:04:58.504
I expect you to know why.

916
01:04:59.940 --> 01:05:01.226
The Cradle.

917
01:05:01.300 --> 01:05:03.223
<i>This is the next thing. Tony.</i>

918
01:05:03.380 --> 01:05:06.350
This is the next me.

919
01:05:06.740 --> 01:05:09.311
The Regeneration Cradle prints tissue.

920
01:05:09.420 --> 01:05:11.070
It can't build a living body.

921
01:05:11.180 --> 01:05:12.261
It can. You can.

922
01:05:12.740 --> 01:05:14.026
You lack the materials.

923
01:05:16.460 --> 01:05:17.825
You're a brilliant woman. Helen.

924
01:05:21.100 --> 01:05:24.183
But we all have room to improve.

925
01:05:45.980 --> 01:05:48.381
I didn't realise you were waiting.

926
01:05:48.500 --> 01:05:52.903
I would've joined you.
but it didn't seem like the right time.

927
01:05:53.860 --> 01:05:55.942
They used up all the hot water.

928
01:05:56.780 --> 01:05:58.225
I should've joined you.

929
01:05:58.380 --> 01:06:00.030
Missed our window.

930
01:06:00.820 --> 01:06:02.060
Did we?

931
01:06:05.620 --> 01:06:06.746
The world just saw the Hulk.

932
01:06:09.420 --> 01:06:11.343
The real Hulk. for the first time.

933
01:06:14.580 --> 01:06:17.231
- You know I have to leave.
- You assume that I have to stay?

934
01:06:19.300 --> 01:06:21.951
I had this dream.

935
01:06:22.300 --> 01:06:24.268
The kind that seems normal at the time.

936
01:06:25.500 --> 01:06:26.740
but when you wake...

937
01:06:26.940 --> 01:06:28.271
What did you dream?

938
01:06:29.300 --> 01:06:31.109
That I was an Avenger.

939
01:06:33.140 --> 01:06:36.947
That I was anything more
than the assassin they made me.

940
01:06:38.420 --> 01:06:40.502
I think you're being hard on yourself.

941
01:06:42.620 --> 01:06:45.100
Here I was hoping that was your job.

942
01:06:48.060 --> 01:06:49.630
What are you doing?

943
01:06:51.260 --> 01:06:53.069
I'm running with it.

944
01:06:54.380 --> 01:06:55.984
With you.

945
01:06:56.740 --> 01:06:59.061
If running is the plan.

946
01:07:00.180 --> 01:07:01.944
as far as you want.

947
01:07:03.820 --> 01:07:05.584
Are you out of your mind?

948
01:07:10.940 --> 01:07:12.351
I want you to understand that...

949
01:07:12.460 --> 01:07:13.871
Natasha.

950
01:07:14.980 --> 01:07:16.425
where can I go?

951
01:07:17.500 --> 01:07:19.821
Where in the world am I not a threat?

952
01:07:19.940 --> 01:07:22.261
- You're not a threat to me.
- Are you sure?

953
01:07:23.180 --> 01:07:24.989
Even if I didn't just...

954
01:07:26.620 --> 01:07:27.985
There's no future with me.

955
01:07:29.660 --> 01:07:30.661
I can't ever...

956
01:07:30.900 --> 01:07:33.141
I can't have this.

957
01:07:33.860 --> 01:07:34.986
Kids.

958
01:07:35.460 --> 01:07:38.031
Do the math. I physically can't.

959
01:07:39.780 --> 01:07:41.225
Neither can I.

960
01:07:45.900 --> 01:07:49.427
In the Red Room where I was trained...

961
01:07:49.900 --> 01:07:52.380
Where I was raised.

962
01:07:53.340 --> 01:07:55.991
they have a graduation ceremony.

963
01:07:57.620 --> 01:07:59.429
They sterilise you.

964
01:08:02.660 --> 01:08:04.071
It's efficient.

965
01:08:06.980 --> 01:08:08.345
One less thing to worry about.

966
01:08:10.460 --> 01:08:13.828
The one thing
that might matter more than a mission.

967
01:08:16.180 --> 01:08:18.069
Makes everything easier.

968
01:08:19.460 --> 01:08:20.700
Even killing.

969
01:08:25.780 --> 01:08:28.863
You still think
you're the only monster on the team?

970
01:08:35.060 --> 01:08:37.142
So. we disappear?

971
01:08:43.820 --> 01:08:45.660
Thor didn't say
where he was going for answers?

972
01:08:46.500 --> 01:08:49.026
Sometimes my teammates
don't tell me things.

973
01:08:50.140 --> 01:08:52.188
I was kind of hoping
Thor would be the exception.

974
01:08:52.300 --> 01:08:54.302
Yeah. give him time.

975
01:08:54.460 --> 01:08:56.383
We don't know
what the Maximoff kid showed him.

976
01:08:58.580 --> 01:09:00.184
"Earth's mightiest heroes."

977
01:09:00.340 --> 01:09:01.944
Pulled us apart like cotton candy.

978
01:09:02.300 --> 01:09:03.780
Seems like you walked away all right.

979
01:09:06.220 --> 01:09:07.221
Is that a problem?

980
01:09:07.580 --> 01:09:09.503
I don't trust a guy without a dark side.

981
01:09:10.700 --> 01:09:11.747
Call me old-fashioned.

982
01:09:11.860 --> 01:09:14.431
Well. let's just say
you haven't seen it yet.

983
01:09:14.740 --> 01:09:16.947
You know Ultron is trying
to tear us apart. right?

984
01:09:17.180 --> 01:09:19.421
Well. I guess you'd know.

985
01:09:19.540 --> 01:09:20.826
Whether you'd tell us
is a bit of a question.

986
01:09:20.980 --> 01:09:22.106
Banner and I were doing research.

987
01:09:22.260 --> 01:09:24.460
- That would affect the team.
- That would end the team!

988
01:09:24.700 --> 01:09:25.781
Isn't that the mission?

989
01:09:25.980 --> 01:09:27.220
Isn't that the "Why We Fight"?

990
01:09:27.340 --> 01:09:29.581
So we can end the fight.
So we get to go home!

991
01:09:32.820 --> 01:09:35.187
Every time someone tries
to win a war before it starts.

992
01:09:35.300 --> 01:09:36.870
innocent people die.

993
01:09:36.980 --> 01:09:37.981
Every time.

994
01:09:40.460 --> 01:09:42.861
I'm sorry. Mr Stark...

995
01:09:43.740 --> 01:09:44.900
Clint said you wouldn't mind.

996
01:09:44.940 --> 01:09:47.466
but our tractor doesn't seem
to want to start at all.

997
01:09:47.780 --> 01:09:50.140
- I thought maybe you might...
- Yeah. I'll give her a kick.

998
01:09:53.580 --> 01:09:55.150
Don't take from my pile.

999
01:10:05.380 --> 01:10:06.541
Hello. Deere.

1000
01:10:09.420 --> 01:10:10.831
Tell me everything.

1001
01:10:12.060 --> 01:10:13.425
What ails you?

1002
01:10:13.660 --> 01:10:14.661
Do me a favour.

1003
01:10:16.940 --> 01:10:18.829
Try not to bring it to life.

1004
01:10:18.980 --> 01:10:20.505
Why. Ms Barton. you little minx.

1005
01:10:20.860 --> 01:10:23.386
I get it. Maria Hill called you. right?

1006
01:10:23.500 --> 01:10:24.820
Was she ever not working for you?

1007
01:10:24.900 --> 01:10:26.390
Artificial intelligence.

1008
01:10:27.420 --> 01:10:29.070
You never even hesitated.

1009
01:10:29.380 --> 01:10:30.740
Look. it's been a really long day.

1010
01:10:30.820 --> 01:10:32.424
like Eugene O'Neill long.

1011
01:10:32.540 --> 01:10:34.700
so how's about
we skip to the part where you're useful.

1012
01:10:34.740 --> 01:10:37.340
Look me in the eye and tell me
you're going to shut him down.

1013
01:10:37.660 --> 01:10:39.071
You're not the director of me.

1014
01:10:39.180 --> 01:10:41.023
I'm not the director of anybody.

1015
01:10:41.340 --> 01:10:42.944
I'm just an old man

1016
01:10:43.620 --> 01:10:45.190
who cares very much about you.

1017
01:10:48.060 --> 01:10:49.869
And I'm the man
who killed the Avengers.

1018
01:10:51.700 --> 01:10:52.826
I saw it.

1019
01:10:53.020 --> 01:10:54.590
I didn't tell the team. How could I?

1020
01:10:55.860 --> 01:10:57.703
I saw them all dead. Nick. I felt it.

1021
01:10:58.060 --> 01:10:59.585
The whole world. too.

1022
01:11:00.020 --> 01:11:01.021
Because of me.

1023
01:11:02.260 --> 01:11:03.705
I wasn't ready.

1024
01:11:05.180 --> 01:11:06.591
I didn't do all I could.

1025
01:11:07.620 --> 01:11:09.702
Maximoff girl. she's working you. Stark.

1026
01:11:10.340 --> 01:11:13.822
- Playing on your fear.
- I wasn't tricked. I was shown.

1027
01:11:13.940 --> 01:11:16.227
Wasn't a nightmare. it was my legacy.

1028
01:11:16.540 --> 01:11:18.702
The end of the path I started us on.

1029
01:11:19.580 --> 01:11:21.820
You come up with some pretty
impressive inventions. Tony.

1030
01:11:23.980 --> 01:11:25.391
War isn't one of them.

1031
01:11:28.980 --> 01:11:30.425
I watched my friends die.

1032
01:11:30.700 --> 01:11:32.702
You'd think that'd be
as bad as it gets. right?

1033
01:11:34.140 --> 01:11:35.585
Nope.

1034
01:11:36.580 --> 01:11:39.106
- It wasn't the worst part.
- The worst part

1035
01:11:40.140 --> 01:11:41.426
is that you didn't.

1036
01:11:48.140 --> 01:11:49.221
I'll see you tonight.

1037
01:11:51.980 --> 01:11:53.266
I like the look.

1038
01:11:54.420 --> 01:11:56.946
If you're going for inconspicuous.
though. near miss.

1039
01:11:57.300 --> 01:11:58.347
I need your help.

1040
01:11:58.580 --> 01:11:59.581
It's nice to be needed.

1041
01:11:59.980 --> 01:12:01.345
It's dangerous.

1042
01:12:01.980 --> 01:12:03.709
I'd be disappointed if it wasn't.

1043
01:12:06.620 --> 01:12:09.942
Ultron took you folks out of play
to buy himself time.

1044
01:12:10.300 --> 01:12:13.270
My contacts all say
he's building something.

1045
01:12:13.380 --> 01:12:15.986
The amount of vibranium
he made off with.

1046
01:12:16.100 --> 01:12:17.590
I don't think it's just one thing.

1047
01:12:17.700 --> 01:12:19.031
What about Ultron himself?

1048
01:12:19.140 --> 01:12:21.507
He's easy to track. He's everywhere.

1049
01:12:21.940 --> 01:12:24.307
The guy is multiplying faster
than a Catholic rabbit.

1050
01:12:24.980 --> 01:12:27.790
It still doesn't help us get an angle
on any of his plans. though.

1051
01:12:28.020 --> 01:12:29.101
Is he still going after launch codes?

1052
01:12:29.380 --> 01:12:30.745
Yes. he is.

1053
01:12:30.860 --> 01:12:32.350
But he's not making any headway.

1054
01:12:32.460 --> 01:12:34.542
I cracked the Pentagon's firewall
in high school on a dare.

1055
01:12:34.660 --> 01:12:37.266
Well. I contacted our friends
at the Nexus about that.

1056
01:12:37.340 --> 01:12:38.341
Nexus?

1057
01:12:38.460 --> 01:12:40.110
It's the world Internet hub in Oslo.

1058
01:12:40.540 --> 01:12:42.304
Every byte of data flows through there.

1059
01:12:42.540 --> 01:12:43.587
Fastest access on Earth.

1060
01:12:43.740 --> 01:12:44.787
So. what did they say?

1061
01:12:45.020 --> 01:12:46.784
He's fixated on the missiles.

1062
01:12:47.020 --> 01:12:48.700
But the codes
are constantly being changed.

1063
01:12:49.180 --> 01:12:50.181
By whom?

1064
01:12:51.420 --> 01:12:52.626
Parties unknown.

1065
01:12:52.820 --> 01:12:53.946
Do we have an ally?

1066
01:12:54.060 --> 01:12:56.381
Ultron's got an enemy.
That's not the same thing.

1067
01:12:56.740 --> 01:12:58.583
Still. I'd pay folding money
to know who it is.

1068
01:12:58.700 --> 01:12:59.861
I might need to visit Oslo.

1069
01:13:00.340 --> 01:13:01.501
Find our unknown.

1070
01:13:01.660 --> 01:13:03.105
Well. this is good times. boss.

1071
01:13:03.220 --> 01:13:04.506
but I was kind of hoping when I saw you.

1072
01:13:04.620 --> 01:13:05.660
you'd have more than that.

1073
01:13:05.900 --> 01:13:07.902
I do. I have you.

1074
01:13:08.780 --> 01:13:11.986
Back in the day. I had eyes everywhere.
Ears. everywhere else.

1075
01:13:12.340 --> 01:13:15.344
You kids had all the tech
you could dream up.

1076
01:13:16.340 --> 01:13:18.342
Here we all are. back on Earth.

1077
01:13:18.580 --> 01:13:22.070
with nothing but our wit
and our will to save the world.

1078
01:13:23.660 --> 01:13:25.822
Ultron says the Avengers
are the only thing

1079
01:13:26.020 --> 01:13:27.465
between him and his mission.

1080
01:13:27.580 --> 01:13:29.742
And whether or not he admits it.

1081
01:13:29.900 --> 01:13:32.631
his mission is global destruction.

1082
01:13:33.860 --> 01:13:36.022
All this. laid in a grave.

1083
01:13:38.060 --> 01:13:39.744
So stand.

1084
01:13:40.540 --> 01:13:42.269
Outwit the platinum bastard.

1085
01:13:42.900 --> 01:13:44.380
Steve doesn't like that kind of talk.

1086
01:13:44.580 --> 01:13:45.661
You know what. Romanoff?

1087
01:13:46.860 --> 01:13:48.191
So. what does he want?

1088
01:13:49.900 --> 01:13:51.629
To become better.

1089
01:13:51.740 --> 01:13:53.105
Better than us.

1090
01:13:53.460 --> 01:13:55.861
- He keeps building bodies.
- Person bodies.

1091
01:13:56.460 --> 01:13:58.064
The human form is inefficient.

1092
01:13:58.220 --> 01:14:00.382
Biologically speaking. we're outmoded.

1093
01:14:00.500 --> 01:14:02.468
But he keeps coming back to it.

1094
01:14:02.580 --> 01:14:04.700
When you two programmed him
to protect the human race.

1095
01:14:04.740 --> 01:14:06.071
you amazingly failed.

1096
01:14:06.380 --> 01:14:08.223
They don't need to be protected.

1097
01:14:08.940 --> 01:14:10.430
They need to evolve.

1098
01:14:12.580 --> 01:14:14.548
Ultron's going to evolve.

1099
01:14:14.740 --> 01:14:15.787
How?

1100
01:14:17.100 --> 01:14:19.785
Has anyone been in contact
with Helen Cho?

1101
01:14:23.540 --> 01:14:25.190
It's beautiful.

1102
01:14:25.620 --> 01:14:28.544
The vibranium atoms aren't just
compatible with the tissue cells.

1103
01:14:28.660 --> 01:14:29.900
they're binding them.

1104
01:14:30.380 --> 01:14:31.666
And S.H.I.E.L.D.
never even thought to...

1105
01:14:31.900 --> 01:14:34.471
The most versatile substance
on the planet.

1106
01:14:34.580 --> 01:14:37.060
and they used it to make a Frisbee.

1107
01:14:37.260 --> 01:14:38.386
Typical of humans.

1108
01:14:38.580 --> 01:14:41.106
They scratch the surface
and never think

1109
01:14:43.060 --> 01:14:44.585
to look within.

1110
01:14:55.100 --> 01:14:56.545
I'll take Natasha and Clint.

1111
01:14:56.780 --> 01:14:59.986
All right. Strictly recon. I'll hit the Nexus.
I'll join you as soon as I can.

1112
01:15:00.100 --> 01:15:01.625
If Ultron's really building a body...

1113
01:15:01.860 --> 01:15:03.385
He'll be more powerful than any of us.

1114
01:15:03.580 --> 01:15:04.661
Maybe all of us.

1115
01:15:05.180 --> 01:15:06.989
An android designed by a robot.

1116
01:15:07.220 --> 01:15:08.346
You know. I really miss the days

1117
01:15:08.500 --> 01:15:10.628
when the weirdest thing
science ever created was me.

1118
01:15:11.220 --> 01:15:12.870
I'll drop Banner off at the tower.

1119
01:15:13.020 --> 01:15:14.306
You mind if I borrow Ms Hill?

1120
01:15:14.540 --> 01:15:16.304
She's all yours. Apparently.

1121
01:15:16.460 --> 01:15:17.621
What are you gonna do?

1122
01:15:17.780 --> 01:15:20.863
I don't know.
Something dramatic. I hope.

1123
01:15:24.220 --> 01:15:27.904
I'm gonna finish reflooring that sunroom
as soon as I get back.

1124
01:15:28.140 --> 01:15:30.791
Yeah. then you'll find
another part of the house to tear apart.

1125
01:15:30.980 --> 01:15:32.141
No.

1126
01:15:32.780 --> 01:15:34.305
It's the last project.

1127
01:15:35.820 --> 01:15:36.821
I promise.

1128
01:15:55.100 --> 01:15:56.625
So. this is it.

1129
01:15:58.260 --> 01:16:00.501
The Water of Sight.

1130
01:16:02.820 --> 01:16:05.221
In every realm. there's a reflection.

1131
01:16:06.420 --> 01:16:07.751
If the water's spirits accept me.

1132
01:16:07.900 --> 01:16:09.868
I can return to my dream

1133
01:16:10.660 --> 01:16:12.105
and find what I missed.

1134
01:16:12.340 --> 01:16:16.186
Men who enter that water.
the legends don't end well.

1135
01:16:17.860 --> 01:16:19.589
A hacker who's faster than Ultron?

1136
01:16:19.780 --> 01:16:20.827
He could be anywhere.

1137
01:16:20.940 --> 01:16:23.181
and as this is the centre of everything.

1138
01:16:23.300 --> 01:16:26.702
I'm just a guy looking for a needle
in the world's biggest haystack.

1139
01:16:27.700 --> 01:16:29.270
How do you find it?

1140
01:16:29.700 --> 01:16:32.271
It's pretty simple. You bring a magnet.

1141
01:16:34.460 --> 01:16:35.580
<i>I'm decrypting nuclear codes</i>

1142
01:16:35.700 --> 01:16:37.031
<i>And you don't want me to</i>

1143
01:16:39.340 --> 01:16:40.830
Come and get me.

1144
01:16:53.180 --> 01:16:54.227
Wake up!

1145
01:17:01.060 --> 01:17:02.061
Thor!

1146
01:17:02.900 --> 01:17:03.947
Extinction.

1147
01:17:17.420 --> 01:17:19.548
Cellular cohesion
will take a few hours.

1148
01:17:19.740 --> 01:17:22.141
but we can initiate
the consciousness stream.

1149
01:17:22.740 --> 01:17:25.550
We're uploading your cerebral matrix

1150
01:17:25.740 --> 01:17:26.946
now.

1151
01:17:28.420 --> 01:17:29.990
I can read him.

1152
01:17:30.740 --> 01:17:32.265
He's dreaming.

1153
01:17:32.500 --> 01:17:34.309
I wouldn't call it dreams.

1154
01:17:34.540 --> 01:17:36.383
It's Ultron's base consciousness.

1155
01:17:36.580 --> 01:17:38.105
Informational noise. Soon...

1156
01:17:38.340 --> 01:17:39.466
How soon?

1157
01:17:39.700 --> 01:17:41.031
I'm not being pushy.

1158
01:17:41.260 --> 01:17:42.910
We're imprinting a physical brain.

1159
01:17:43.060 --> 01:17:44.505
There are no shortcuts.

1160
01:17:44.780 --> 01:17:45.986
Even if your magic gem...

1161
01:17:56.700 --> 01:17:58.031
How could you?

1162
01:17:58.100 --> 01:17:59.147
How could I what?

1163
01:17:59.420 --> 01:18:02.583
You said we would
destroy the Avengers.

1164
01:18:02.740 --> 01:18:03.787
make a better world.

1165
01:18:04.100 --> 01:18:05.147
It will be better.

1166
01:18:06.100 --> 01:18:08.467
- When everyone is dead?
- That is not...

1167
01:18:09.420 --> 01:18:13.266
The human race will have
every opportunity to improve.

1168
01:18:13.780 --> 01:18:15.111
And if they don't?

1169
01:18:15.300 --> 01:18:16.426
Ask Noah.

1170
01:18:17.620 --> 01:18:18.667
You are a madman.

1171
01:18:18.780 --> 01:18:22.227
There were more than a dozen
extinction-level events

1172
01:18:22.380 --> 01:18:25.463
before even the dinosaurs got theirs.

1173
01:18:25.580 --> 01:18:27.742
When the Earth starts to settle.

1174
01:18:28.260 --> 01:18:30.149
God throws a stone at it.

1175
01:18:30.300 --> 01:18:32.621
And. believe me. he's winding up.

1176
01:18:33.380 --> 01:18:34.586
We have to evolve.

1177
01:18:35.140 --> 01:18:36.301
There's no room

1178
01:18:37.140 --> 01:18:38.266
for the weak.

1179
01:18:38.500 --> 01:18:40.468
And who decides who's weak?

1180
01:18:41.340 --> 01:18:43.069
Life.

1181
01:18:43.700 --> 01:18:45.509
Life always decides.

1182
01:18:48.460 --> 01:18:49.507
There's incoming.

1183
01:18:50.980 --> 01:18:54.302
- The Quinjet. We have to move.
- That's not a problem.

1184
01:19:01.300 --> 01:19:02.301
Wait. guys!

1185
01:19:06.340 --> 01:19:07.626
They'll understand.

1186
01:19:07.940 --> 01:19:10.068
When they see. they'll understand.

1187
01:19:10.460 --> 01:19:13.748
I just need a little more time.

1188
01:19:25.140 --> 01:19:27.268
Two minutes. Stay close.

1189
01:19:34.460 --> 01:19:35.461
Dr Cho!

1190
01:19:39.380 --> 01:19:40.905
He's uploading himself into the body.

1191
01:19:41.020 --> 01:19:42.067
Where?

1192
01:19:43.860 --> 01:19:46.431
The real power is inside the Cradle.

1193
01:19:46.500 --> 01:19:47.547
The gem.

1194
01:19:48.300 --> 01:19:51.031
its power is uncontainable.

1195
01:19:51.900 --> 01:19:53.550
You can't just blow it up.

1196
01:19:54.500 --> 01:19:56.741
You have to get the Cradle to Stark.

1197
01:19:56.860 --> 01:19:57.907
First. I have to find it.

1198
01:19:58.220 --> 01:19:59.221
Go.

1199
01:19:59.580 --> 01:20:00.820
<i>Did you guys copy that?</i>

1200
01:20:00.980 --> 01:20:02.061
We did.

1201
01:20:02.220 --> 01:20:04.666
I got a private jet taking off across town.

1202
01:20:05.020 --> 01:20:06.306
No manifest.

1203
01:20:06.420 --> 01:20:07.467
That could be him.

1204
01:20:08.420 --> 01:20:09.990
There. It's a truck from the lab.

1205
01:20:10.140 --> 01:20:11.346
Right above you. Cap.

1206
01:20:11.620 --> 01:20:13.429
On the loop by the bridge.

1207
01:20:14.020 --> 01:20:15.021
It's them.

1208
01:20:15.180 --> 01:20:16.980
You got three with the Cradle.
one in the cab.

1209
01:20:17.740 --> 01:20:18.860
I could take out the driver.

1210
01:20:18.900 --> 01:20:20.060
<i>Negative. That truck crashes.</i>

1211
01:20:20.100 --> 01:20:21.670
the gem could level the city.

1212
01:20:22.100 --> 01:20:23.340
<i>We need to draw out Ultron.</i>

1213
01:20:33.060 --> 01:20:35.108
No. no. no. no.

1214
01:20:36.940 --> 01:20:37.987
Leave me alone!

1215
01:20:46.620 --> 01:20:48.304
Well. he's definitely unhappy.

1216
01:20:48.460 --> 01:20:49.950
I'm gonna try and keep him that way.

1217
01:20:50.060 --> 01:20:51.340
You're not a match for him. Cap.

1218
01:20:52.460 --> 01:20:53.541
Thanks. Barton.

1219
01:21:16.260 --> 01:21:17.500
You know what's in that cradle?

1220
01:21:18.820 --> 01:21:20.549
The power to make real change.

1221
01:21:20.660 --> 01:21:22.071
And that terrifies you.

1222
01:21:22.220 --> 01:21:23.380
I wouldn't call it a comfort.

1223
01:21:26.620 --> 01:21:27.667
Stop it.

1224
01:21:38.500 --> 01:21:41.185
We got a window. Four. three...

1225
01:21:41.820 --> 01:21:42.821
Give him hell.

1226
01:21:53.780 --> 01:21:55.260
I'm always picking up after you boys.

1227
01:21:56.860 --> 01:21:58.510
They're heading under the overpass.
I've got no shot.

1228
01:21:58.860 --> 01:21:59.907
<i>Which way?</i>

1229
01:22:00.100 --> 01:22:01.101
Hard right.

1230
01:22:02.260 --> 01:22:03.341
Now.

1231
01:22:34.220 --> 01:22:36.507
Out of the way! Coming through!
Sorry. coming through!

1232
01:22:52.260 --> 01:22:53.421
Come on!

1233
01:22:53.900 --> 01:22:55.345
Clint. can you draw out the guards?

1234
01:22:55.460 --> 01:22:56.507
Let's find out.

1235
01:22:57.540 --> 01:22:58.587
Beep. beep!

1236
01:23:36.060 --> 01:23:37.630
They're heading back towards you.

1237
01:23:37.780 --> 01:23:39.340
So whatever you're gonna do. do it now.

1238
01:23:44.820 --> 01:23:47.471
<i>I'm going in.
Cap. can you keep him occupied?</i>

1239
01:23:47.620 --> 01:23:49.509
What do you think I've been doing?

1240
01:24:33.100 --> 01:24:35.228
<i>Okay. package is airborne.</i>

1241
01:24:35.940 --> 01:24:37.021
I have a clean shot.

1242
01:24:37.460 --> 01:24:38.825
Negative. I am still in the truck.

1243
01:24:38.980 --> 01:24:39.981
- What the hell are you...
- Just be ready.

1244
01:24:40.140 --> 01:24:41.380
I'm sending the package to you.

1245
01:24:41.860 --> 01:24:43.060
How do you want me to take it?

1246
01:24:43.260 --> 01:24:45.342
You might wish you hadn't asked that.

1247
01:24:58.140 --> 01:24:59.869
Please. don't do this.

1248
01:25:00.380 --> 01:25:01.950
What choice do we have?

1249
01:25:10.220 --> 01:25:11.221
I lost him!

1250
01:25:11.380 --> 01:25:12.745
He's headed your way!

1251
01:25:17.700 --> 01:25:18.747
Nat. we gotta go.

1252
01:25:30.060 --> 01:25:31.869
Nat!

1253
01:25:35.900 --> 01:25:36.901
Cap. you see Nat?

1254
01:25:37.860 --> 01:25:40.431
If you have the package.
get it to Stark! Go!

1255
01:25:40.740 --> 01:25:41.901
Do you have eyes on Nat?

1256
01:25:42.060 --> 01:25:43.061
<i>Go!</i>

1257
01:25:45.060 --> 01:25:46.061
Damn it.

1258
01:25:46.580 --> 01:25:47.661
Civilians in our path.

1259
01:25:48.940 --> 01:25:50.465
Can you stop this thing?

1260
01:26:29.340 --> 01:26:30.671
I'm fine.

1261
01:26:30.780 --> 01:26:32.464
I just need to take a minute.

1262
01:26:32.940 --> 01:26:34.829
I'm very tempted not to give you one.

1263
01:26:34.980 --> 01:26:36.869
The Cradle. Did you get it?

1264
01:26:37.060 --> 01:26:38.550
Stark will take care of it.

1265
01:26:39.940 --> 01:26:40.941
No. he won't.

1266
01:26:44.460 --> 01:26:46.747
You don't know what you're talking
about. Stark's not crazy.

1267
01:26:46.820 --> 01:26:48.948
He will do anything to make things right.

1268
01:26:53.820 --> 01:26:55.106
Stark. come in.

1269
01:26:55.620 --> 01:26:56.667
Stark.

1270
01:26:57.980 --> 01:26:59.106
Anyone on comms.

1271
01:26:59.220 --> 01:27:00.665
Ultron can't tell the difference

1272
01:27:00.820 --> 01:27:03.141
between saving the world
and destroying it.

1273
01:27:05.060 --> 01:27:07.506
Where do you think he gets that?

1274
01:27:09.700 --> 01:27:11.270
- Anything on Nat?
- I haven't heard.

1275
01:27:11.380 --> 01:27:13.747
But she's alive. or Ultron would
be rubbing our faces in it.

1276
01:27:13.860 --> 01:27:15.191
This is sealed tight.

1277
01:27:15.340 --> 01:27:16.860
We're gonna need
to access the program.

1278
01:27:16.900 --> 01:27:18.823
break it down from within.

1279
01:27:20.060 --> 01:27:22.786
Any chance Natasha might leave you
a message outside the Internet?

1280
01:27:22.900 --> 01:27:23.947
Old-school spy stuff?

1281
01:27:24.420 --> 01:27:26.229
There are some nets I can cast.

1282
01:27:26.340 --> 01:27:27.580
Yeah. I'll find her.

1283
01:27:30.180 --> 01:27:31.944
I can work on tissue degeneration

1284
01:27:32.060 --> 01:27:35.269
if you could fry whatever
operational system Cho implanted.

1285
01:27:35.420 --> 01:27:36.546
Yeah. about that.

1286
01:27:40.980 --> 01:27:41.981
No.

1287
01:27:42.180 --> 01:27:44.023
- You have to trust me.
- Kind of don't.

1288
01:27:44.180 --> 01:27:48.230
Our ally. the guy protecting
the military's nuclear codes.

1289
01:27:50.180 --> 01:27:51.181
I found him.

1290
01:27:51.260 --> 01:27:52.386
<i>Hello. Dr Banner.</i>

1291
01:27:53.260 --> 01:27:55.501
Ultron didn't go after Jarvis
because he was angry.

1292
01:27:56.100 --> 01:27:59.707
He attacked him because he was
scared of what he can do.

1293
01:28:00.860 --> 01:28:02.510
So Jarvis went underground.

1294
01:28:02.620 --> 01:28:04.110
Scattered. dumped his memory.

1295
01:28:04.700 --> 01:28:06.190
But not his protocols.

1296
01:28:06.620 --> 01:28:10.067
He didn't even know he was in there
until I pieced him together.

1297
01:28:12.900 --> 01:28:17.701
So. you want me to help you
put Jarvis into this thing?

1298
01:28:17.820 --> 01:28:19.584
No! Of course not.

1299
01:28:19.740 --> 01:28:21.424
I wanna help you put Jarvis in this thing.

1300
01:28:23.820 --> 01:28:25.470
We're out of my field. here.

1301
01:28:25.580 --> 01:28:27.582
You know bio-organics
better than anyone.

1302
01:28:27.900 --> 01:28:30.790
And you just assume
that Jarvis's operational matrix

1303
01:28:30.900 --> 01:28:32.345
can beat Ultron's?

1304
01:28:32.460 --> 01:28:35.748
Jarvis has been beating him from inside
without knowing it.

1305
01:28:35.900 --> 01:28:36.901
This is the opportunity.

1306
01:28:36.980 --> 01:28:38.744
We can create Ultron's perfect self

1307
01:28:38.900 --> 01:28:42.382
without the homicidal glitches
he thinks are his winning personality.

1308
01:28:42.500 --> 01:28:44.582
- We have to.
<i>- I believe it's worth a go.</i>

1309
01:28:47.180 --> 01:28:48.261
I'm in a loop!

1310
01:28:48.420 --> 01:28:51.390
I'm caught in a time loop.
This is exactly where it all went wrong.

1311
01:28:51.500 --> 01:28:53.420
I know. I know. I know
what everyone's gonna say.

1312
01:28:53.500 --> 01:28:55.468
But they're already saying it.

1313
01:28:56.020 --> 01:28:57.181
We're mad scientists.

1314
01:28:57.940 --> 01:29:00.671
We're monsters. buddy.
We've gotta own it.

1315
01:29:01.660 --> 01:29:02.900
Make a stand.

1316
01:29:08.300 --> 01:29:09.790
It's not a loop.

1317
01:29:11.020 --> 01:29:12.784
It's the end of the line.

1318
01:29:33.300 --> 01:29:35.428
I wasn't sure you would wake up.

1319
01:29:35.540 --> 01:29:38.987
I hoped you would.
I wanted to show you.

1320
01:29:39.140 --> 01:29:40.824
I don't have anyone else.

1321
01:29:43.660 --> 01:29:47.267
I think a lot about meteors.
The purity in them.

1322
01:29:47.420 --> 01:29:48.945
Boom! The end.

1323
01:29:49.420 --> 01:29:50.831
Start again.

1324
01:29:50.980 --> 01:29:52.948
The world made clean

1325
01:29:53.060 --> 01:29:55.381
for the new man to rebuild.

1326
01:29:55.700 --> 01:29:57.828
I was meant to be new.

1327
01:29:58.700 --> 01:30:01.306
I was meant to be beautiful.

1328
01:30:01.860 --> 01:30:03.988
The world would have looked to the sky

1329
01:30:04.100 --> 01:30:05.340
and seen hope.

1330
01:30:05.700 --> 01:30:07.031
seen mercy.

1331
01:30:07.820 --> 01:30:09.902
Instead. they'll look up in horror

1332
01:30:10.020 --> 01:30:11.351
because of you.

1333
01:30:11.540 --> 01:30:13.349
You've wounded me.

1334
01:30:14.020 --> 01:30:15.704
I give you full marks for that.

1335
01:30:16.340 --> 01:30:19.264
But. like the man said.
what doesn't kill me...

1336
01:30:24.500 --> 01:30:25.831
...just makes me stronger.

1337
01:31:05.900 --> 01:31:08.062
This framework is not compatible.

1338
01:31:08.220 --> 01:31:10.905
The genetic coding tower is at 97%.

1339
01:31:11.020 --> 01:31:14.866
You have got to upload that schematic
in the next three minutes.

1340
01:31:17.140 --> 01:31:19.063
- I'm gonna say this once.
- How about "none-ce"?

1341
01:31:19.260 --> 01:31:21.308
- Shut it down!
- Nope. not gonna happen.

1342
01:31:21.420 --> 01:31:22.581
You don't know what you're doing.

1343
01:31:22.740 --> 01:31:24.071
And you do?

1344
01:31:24.420 --> 01:31:25.421
She's not in your head?

1345
01:31:25.580 --> 01:31:27.230
I know you're angry.

1346
01:31:27.340 --> 01:31:28.705
We're way past that.

1347
01:31:28.820 --> 01:31:31.266
I could choke the life out of you
and never change a shade.

1348
01:31:31.500 --> 01:31:33.180
Banner. after everything
that's happened...

1349
01:31:33.260 --> 01:31:34.625
It's nothing compared to what's coming!

1350
01:31:34.740 --> 01:31:37.107
- You don't know what's in there.
- This isn't a game!

1351
01:31:40.420 --> 01:31:41.831
No. no. Go on.

1352
01:31:42.780 --> 01:31:44.703
You were saying?

1353
01:31:50.940 --> 01:31:51.987
Pietro!

1354
01:31:52.540 --> 01:31:53.621
What?

1355
01:31:54.020 --> 01:31:55.590
You didn't see that coming?

1356
01:31:57.780 --> 01:31:58.941
I'm rerouting the upload.

1357
01:32:05.260 --> 01:32:07.024
Go ahead. piss me off.

1358
01:32:19.340 --> 01:32:20.466
Wait!

1359
01:33:45.140 --> 01:33:47.381
I am sorry. That was

1360
01:33:48.380 --> 01:33:49.791
odd.

1361
01:33:50.020 --> 01:33:51.260
Thank you.

1362
01:33:56.180 --> 01:33:57.227
Thor.

1363
01:33:58.740 --> 01:34:01.346
- You helped create this?
- I've had a vision.

1364
01:34:01.580 --> 01:34:05.301
A whirlpool that sucks in all hope of life.
and at its centre is that.

1365
01:34:06.260 --> 01:34:07.261
What? The gem?

1366
01:34:07.420 --> 01:34:09.991
It's the Mind Stone.
It's one of the six Infinity Stones.

1367
01:34:10.140 --> 01:34:11.380
The greatest power in the universe.

1368
01:34:11.500 --> 01:34:13.662
unparalleled in
its destructive capabilities.

1369
01:34:13.780 --> 01:34:15.748
- Then why would you bring...
- Because Stark is right.

1370
01:34:15.940 --> 01:34:18.386
It's definitely the end times.

1371
01:34:18.580 --> 01:34:19.741
The Avengers cannot defeat Ultron.

1372
01:34:19.900 --> 01:34:21.140
Not alone.

1373
01:34:21.540 --> 01:34:23.463
Why does your Vision sound like Jarvis?

1374
01:34:23.580 --> 01:34:26.265
We reconfigured Jarvis's matrix

1375
01:34:26.780 --> 01:34:28.544
to create something new.

1376
01:34:28.780 --> 01:34:30.464
I think I've had my fill of new.

1377
01:34:30.620 --> 01:34:32.907
You think I'm a child of Ultron.

1378
01:34:33.260 --> 01:34:34.546
You're not?

1379
01:34:35.700 --> 01:34:37.270
I'm not Ultron.

1380
01:34:37.900 --> 01:34:40.107
I am not Jarvis. I am...

1381
01:34:42.220 --> 01:34:43.631
I am.

1382
01:34:45.540 --> 01:34:46.666
I looked in your head

1383
01:34:47.380 --> 01:34:49.144
and saw annihilation.

1384
01:34:49.300 --> 01:34:50.665
Look again.

1385
01:34:50.780 --> 01:34:52.300
Her seal of approval means jack to me.

1386
01:34:52.780 --> 01:34:54.782
Their powers. the horrors in our heads.

1387
01:34:54.940 --> 01:34:56.988
Ultron himself. they all came
from the Mind Stone.

1388
01:34:57.140 --> 01:34:59.302
And they're nothing
compared to what it can unleash.

1389
01:34:59.460 --> 01:35:00.985
- But with it on our side...
- Is it?

1390
01:35:02.420 --> 01:35:03.581
Are you?

1391
01:35:04.460 --> 01:35:05.905
On our side?

1392
01:35:07.780 --> 01:35:09.669
I don't think it's that simple.

1393
01:35:09.820 --> 01:35:12.266
Well. it better
get real simple real soon.

1394
01:35:13.420 --> 01:35:15.548
I am on the side of life.

1395
01:35:15.780 --> 01:35:17.145
Ultron isn't.

1396
01:35:17.740 --> 01:35:19.151
He will end it all.

1397
01:35:19.300 --> 01:35:21.223
What's he waiting for?

1398
01:35:21.380 --> 01:35:22.381
- You.
- Where?

1399
01:35:22.820 --> 01:35:23.981
Sokovia.

1400
01:35:24.100 --> 01:35:25.181
He's got Nat there. too.

1401
01:35:27.340 --> 01:35:28.990
If we're wrong about you.

1402
01:35:31.660 --> 01:35:33.660
if you're the monster
that Ultron made you to be...

1403
01:35:34.180 --> 01:35:35.705
What will you do?

1404
01:35:42.340 --> 01:35:44.422
I don't want to kill Ultron.

1405
01:35:44.820 --> 01:35:48.142
He's unique and he's in pain.

1406
01:35:49.700 --> 01:35:52.271
But that pain will roll over the Earth.

1407
01:35:52.820 --> 01:35:55.107
So. he must be destroyed.

1408
01:35:55.340 --> 01:35:58.264
Every form he's built.
every trace of his presence on the net.

1409
01:35:58.540 --> 01:36:00.190
We have to act now.

1410
01:36:00.620 --> 01:36:04.545
And not one of us
can do it without the others.

1411
01:36:06.540 --> 01:36:08.463
Maybe I am a monster.

1412
01:36:08.620 --> 01:36:10.861
I don't think I'd know if I were one.

1413
01:36:12.020 --> 01:36:13.624
I'm not what you are.

1414
01:36:14.300 --> 01:36:16.462
and not what you intended.

1415
01:36:17.220 --> 01:36:19.700
So. there may be no way
to make you trust me.

1416
01:36:19.980 --> 01:36:21.391
But we need to go.

1417
01:36:36.180 --> 01:36:37.341
Right.

1418
01:36:37.980 --> 01:36:39.220
Well done.

1419
01:36:40.980 --> 01:36:42.027
Three minutes.

1420
01:36:42.740 --> 01:36:44.390
Get what you need.

1421
01:37:00.220 --> 01:37:01.267
<i>Good evening. boss.</i>

1422
01:37:06.420 --> 01:37:08.104
<i>No way we all get through this.</i>

1423
01:37:08.220 --> 01:37:10.300
<i>If even one tin soldier
is left standing. we've lost.</i>

1424
01:37:11.020 --> 01:37:12.460
There's gonna be blood on the floor.

1425
01:37:12.500 --> 01:37:13.911
I got no plans tomorrow night.

1426
01:37:14.020 --> 01:37:15.340
I get first crack at the big guy.

1427
01:37:15.780 --> 01:37:17.270
Iron Man's the one he's waiting for.

1428
01:37:17.380 --> 01:37:19.781
That's true. He hates you the most.

1429
01:37:25.100 --> 01:37:27.262
Ultron knows we're coming.

1430
01:37:27.540 --> 01:37:29.747
Odds are we'll be riding into heavy fire.

1431
01:37:30.260 --> 01:37:31.989
And that's what we signed up for.

1432
01:37:32.260 --> 01:37:34.786
But the people of Sokovia. they didn't.

1433
01:37:35.900 --> 01:37:37.390
<i>So our priority</i>

1434
01:37:38.100 --> 01:37:39.181
<i>is getting them out.</i>

1435
01:37:39.420 --> 01:37:42.344
We're under attack! Clear the city! Now!

1436
01:37:50.140 --> 01:37:51.585
Get off your asses.

1437
01:37:52.820 --> 01:37:54.743
<i>All they want
is to live their lives in peace.</i>

1438
01:37:55.300 --> 01:37:56.660
<i>And that's not gonna happen today.</i>

1439
01:37:58.300 --> 01:38:00.029
<i>But we can do our best to protect them.</i>

1440
01:38:00.740 --> 01:38:02.265
<i>And we can get the job done.</i>

1441
01:38:05.660 --> 01:38:07.947
<i>We find out what Ultron's been building.</i>

1442
01:38:08.900 --> 01:38:10.504
<i>we find Romanoff.</i>

1443
01:38:10.980 --> 01:38:12.823
<i>and we clear the field.</i>

1444
01:38:14.260 --> 01:38:16.183
<i>Keep the fight between us.</i>

1445
01:38:22.900 --> 01:38:25.301
Ultron thinks we're monsters.

1446
01:38:25.820 --> 01:38:28.221
That we're what's wrong with the world.

1447
01:38:28.340 --> 01:38:30.661
This isn't just about beating him.

1448
01:38:31.180 --> 01:38:33.228
It's about whether he's right.

1449
01:38:39.700 --> 01:38:40.747
Natasha!

1450
01:38:41.860 --> 01:38:42.861
Natasha!

1451
01:38:43.020 --> 01:38:44.101
Bruce?

1452
01:38:45.540 --> 01:38:46.541
You all right?

1453
01:38:46.700 --> 01:38:47.747
Yeah.

1454
01:38:47.860 --> 01:38:49.589
The team is in the city.
It's about to light up.

1455
01:38:49.700 --> 01:38:51.860
I don't suppose you found
a key lying around somewhere.

1456
01:38:52.180 --> 01:38:54.308
Yeah. I did.

1457
01:39:00.700 --> 01:39:01.861
So what's our play?

1458
01:39:02.060 --> 01:39:03.425
I'm here to get you to safety.

1459
01:39:04.180 --> 01:39:06.706
- Job's not finished.
- We could help with the evacuation.

1460
01:39:06.860 --> 01:39:08.703
but I can't be in a fight near civilians.

1461
01:39:10.060 --> 01:39:11.221
And you've done plenty.

1462
01:39:13.620 --> 01:39:15.110
Our fight is over.

1463
01:39:16.500 --> 01:39:18.741
So. we just disappear?

1464
01:39:22.900 --> 01:39:24.743
Come on.

1465
01:39:29.540 --> 01:39:31.781
<i>Your man's
in the church. boss.</i>

1466
01:39:31.900 --> 01:39:33.743
<i>I think he's waiting for you.</i>

1467
01:39:37.820 --> 01:39:39.868
Come to confess your sins?

1468
01:39:39.980 --> 01:39:41.220
I don't know. How much time you got?

1469
01:39:41.380 --> 01:39:42.870
More than you.

1470
01:39:45.260 --> 01:39:48.070
Have you been juicing?
Little vibranium cocktail?

1471
01:39:48.180 --> 01:39:50.467
You're looking...
I don't wanna say "puffy."

1472
01:39:50.580 --> 01:39:52.309
You're stalling to protect the people.

1473
01:39:52.700 --> 01:39:55.544
Well. that is the mission. Did you forget?

1474
01:39:55.860 --> 01:39:58.340
I've moved beyond
your mission. I'm free.

1475
01:40:03.100 --> 01:40:04.147
What?

1476
01:40:05.060 --> 01:40:07.381
You think you were
the only one stalling?

1477
01:40:08.100 --> 01:40:09.750
<i>There's the rest
of the vibranium.</i>

1478
01:40:09.860 --> 01:40:11.271
<i>Function. still unclear.</i>

1479
01:40:11.460 --> 01:40:12.621
This is how you end. Tony.

1480
01:40:13.900 --> 01:40:15.664
This is peace in my time.

1481
01:40:32.380 --> 01:40:33.427
Go!

1482
01:40:38.980 --> 01:40:40.311
Get off the bridge!

1483
01:40:44.460 --> 01:40:45.461
Run!

1484
01:40:47.460 --> 01:40:49.269
Ultron.

1485
01:40:54.780 --> 01:40:55.986
My Vision.

1486
01:40:56.220 --> 01:40:58.507
They really did take everything from me.

1487
01:40:58.660 --> 01:41:00.708
You set the terms.
You can change them.

1488
01:41:00.820 --> 01:41:02.060
All right.

1489
01:41:26.260 --> 01:41:27.500
Friday. the Vision?

1490
01:41:27.660 --> 01:41:29.820
<i>Boss. it's working.
He's burning Ultron out of the net.</i>

1491
01:41:29.860 --> 01:41:31.060
<i>He won't escape through there.</i>

1492
01:41:36.140 --> 01:41:37.471
You shut me out.

1493
01:41:37.940 --> 01:41:39.146
You think I care?

1494
01:41:41.140 --> 01:41:42.346
You take away my world.

1495
01:41:43.220 --> 01:41:44.949
I take away yours.

1496
01:42:29.500 --> 01:42:30.706
Friday.

1497
01:42:30.820 --> 01:42:33.266
<i>Sokovia is going for a ride.</i>

1498
01:42:45.780 --> 01:42:47.270
Do you see

1499
01:42:47.740 --> 01:42:49.265
the beauty of it?

1500
01:42:49.860 --> 01:42:51.703
The inevitability.

1501
01:42:51.940 --> 01:42:55.183
You rise. only to fall.

1502
01:42:57.940 --> 01:43:00.784
<i>You. Avengers. you are my meteor.</i>

1503
01:43:01.700 --> 01:43:03.429
<i>My swift and terrible sword.</i>

1504
01:43:03.620 --> 01:43:05.110
<i>And the earth will crack</i>

1505
01:43:05.300 --> 01:43:07.223
<i>with the weight of your failure.</i>

1506
01:43:08.900 --> 01:43:12.666
<i>Purge me from your computers.
turn my own flesh against me.</i>

1507
01:43:13.140 --> 01:43:14.551
<i>It means nothing.</i>

1508
01:43:15.620 --> 01:43:16.985
<i>When the dust settles.</i>

1509
01:43:17.140 --> 01:43:19.029
<i>the only thing living in this world</i>

1510
01:43:19.540 --> 01:43:20.541
<i>will be metal.</i>

1511
01:43:25.100 --> 01:43:26.670
We gotta move.

1512
01:43:26.980 --> 01:43:28.100
You're not gonna turn green?

1513
01:43:28.300 --> 01:43:30.220
I've got a compelling reason
not to lose my cool.

1514
01:43:31.380 --> 01:43:32.666
I adore you.

1515
01:43:41.300 --> 01:43:43.223
But I need the other guy.

1516
01:43:48.060 --> 01:43:49.824
Let's finish the job.

1517
01:44:06.620 --> 01:44:08.031
I really hope this makes us even.

1518
01:44:10.340 --> 01:44:12.388
Now go be a hero.

1519
01:44:20.860 --> 01:44:22.783
<i>The vibranium core's
got a magnetic field.</i>

1520
01:44:22.940 --> 01:44:24.942
<i>That's what's keeping the rock together.</i>

1521
01:44:25.060 --> 01:44:26.107
If it drops?

1522
01:44:26.180 --> 01:44:27.511
<i>Right now. the impact
will kill thousands.</i>

1523
01:44:27.580 --> 01:44:30.311
<i>Once it gets high enough?
Global extinction.</i>

1524
01:44:34.620 --> 01:44:36.702
<i>That building's not clear. The 10th floor.</i>

1525
01:44:41.580 --> 01:44:42.581
Hi.

1526
01:44:43.700 --> 01:44:46.067
Okay. Get in the tub!

1527
01:44:52.900 --> 01:44:54.743
<i>I got airborne.
heading up to the bridge.</i>

1528
01:44:57.540 --> 01:44:58.746
Cap. you got incoming.

1529
01:44:58.900 --> 01:45:00.550
Incoming already came in.

1530
01:45:03.220 --> 01:45:05.700
Stark. you worry about
bringing the city back down safely.

1531
01:45:06.420 --> 01:45:08.229
<i>The rest of us have one job.</i>

1532
01:45:08.380 --> 01:45:09.541
<i>tear these things apart.</i>

1533
01:45:09.860 --> 01:45:11.464
<i>You get hurt. hurt them back.</i>

1534
01:45:12.140 --> 01:45:13.301
<i>You get killed.</i>

1535
01:45:14.340 --> 01:45:15.626
walk it off.

1536
01:45:50.060 --> 01:45:51.266
Go. go. go!

1537
01:45:56.940 --> 01:45:58.704
How could I let this happen?

1538
01:45:58.820 --> 01:46:00.868
- Hey. hey. you okay?
- This is all our fault.

1539
01:46:01.060 --> 01:46:03.260
Hey. look at me.
It's your fault. it's everyone's fault.

1540
01:46:03.300 --> 01:46:04.347
Who cares?

1541
01:46:04.460 --> 01:46:05.985
Are you up for this?

1542
01:46:06.100 --> 01:46:07.181
Are you?

1543
01:46:07.420 --> 01:46:10.827
Look. I just need to know.
Because the city is flying.

1544
01:46:11.140 --> 01:46:15.023
Okay. Look. the city is flying.
we're fighting an army of robots.

1545
01:46:15.940 --> 01:46:17.146
and I have a bow and arrow.

1546
01:46:17.300 --> 01:46:18.381
None of this makes sense.

1547
01:46:21.660 --> 01:46:23.788
But I'm going back out there
because it's my job.

1548
01:46:24.660 --> 01:46:27.311
Okay? And I can't do my job and babysit.

1549
01:46:27.460 --> 01:46:30.464
It doesn't matter
what you did or what you were.

1550
01:46:30.660 --> 01:46:33.266
If you go out there. you fight.
and you fight to kill.

1551
01:46:34.300 --> 01:46:36.940
Stay in here. you're good.
I'll send your brother to come find you.

1552
01:46:36.980 --> 01:46:38.823
But if you step out that door.

1553
01:46:39.740 --> 01:46:40.741
you are an Avenger.

1554
01:46:45.620 --> 01:46:47.429
All right. Good chat.

1555
01:46:51.180 --> 01:46:52.227
Yeah. the city is flying.

1556
01:47:26.220 --> 01:47:27.381
I got you!

1557
01:47:27.700 --> 01:47:28.940
Just look at me!

1558
01:47:35.700 --> 01:47:37.031
<i>You can't save them all.</i>

1559
01:47:38.380 --> 01:47:39.427
You'll never...

1560
01:47:40.700 --> 01:47:43.146
"Never" what? You didn't finish!

1561
01:47:46.900 --> 01:47:48.470
What. were you napping?

1562
01:48:09.940 --> 01:48:11.021
Thor.

1563
01:48:13.620 --> 01:48:15.224
You're bothering me.

1564
01:48:50.620 --> 01:48:51.900
All right. we're all clear here.

1565
01:48:51.980 --> 01:48:53.027
We are not clear!

1566
01:48:53.140 --> 01:48:54.551
We are very not clear!

1567
01:48:57.620 --> 01:48:58.951
All right. coming to you.

1568
01:48:59.420 --> 01:49:01.502
Keep up. old man!

1569
01:49:03.260 --> 01:49:04.785
Nobody would know.

1570
01:49:05.620 --> 01:49:06.667
Nobody.

1571
01:49:08.620 --> 01:49:11.544
"The last I saw him.
an Ultron was sitting on him.

1572
01:49:11.660 --> 01:49:13.549
"Yeah. he'll be missed.
that quick little bastard.

1573
01:49:13.620 --> 01:49:14.621
"I miss him already."

1574
01:49:30.180 --> 01:49:31.341
Hold your fire!

1575
01:49:41.220 --> 01:49:42.267
Romanoff!

1576
01:49:42.780 --> 01:49:43.781
Thanks!

1577
01:49:53.180 --> 01:49:54.784
<i>The anti-gravs
are rigged to flip.</i>

1578
01:49:54.900 --> 01:49:57.062
<i>Touch them. they'll go
full reverse thrust.</i>

1579
01:49:57.180 --> 01:49:58.625
<i>The city's not coming down slow.</i>

1580
01:49:58.740 --> 01:49:59.866
Spire is vibranium.

1581
01:49:59.980 --> 01:50:01.106
If I get Thor to hit it...

1582
01:50:01.380 --> 01:50:02.745
<i>It will crack. That's not enough.</i>

1583
01:50:02.860 --> 01:50:04.385
<i>The impact would still be devastating.</i>

1584
01:50:04.540 --> 01:50:05.900
Maybe if we can cap the other end.

1585
01:50:06.060 --> 01:50:07.710
Keep the atomic action doubling back.

1586
01:50:07.860 --> 01:50:09.225
<i>That could vaporise the city.</i>

1587
01:50:10.220 --> 01:50:12.063
<i>And everyone on it.</i>

1588
01:50:17.900 --> 01:50:19.743
The next wave
is gonna hit any minute.

1589
01:50:19.900 --> 01:50:21.868
- What do you got. Stark?
<i>- Nothing great.</i>

1590
01:50:22.660 --> 01:50:24.901
Maybe a way to blow up the city.

1591
01:50:25.020 --> 01:50:26.306
That'll keep it
from impacting the surface.

1592
01:50:26.420 --> 01:50:27.467
if you guys can get clear.

1593
01:50:27.740 --> 01:50:29.629
I asked for a solution.
not an escape plan.

1594
01:50:29.860 --> 01:50:32.750
<i>Impact radius
is getting bigger every second.</i>

1595
01:50:32.940 --> 01:50:34.305
<i>We're gonna have to make a choice.</i>

1596
01:50:35.060 --> 01:50:36.585
Cap. these people are going nowhere.

1597
01:50:37.420 --> 01:50:40.220
- If Stark finds a way to blow this rock...
- Not till everyone's safe.

1598
01:50:40.620 --> 01:50:43.624
Everyone up here versus everyone
down there? There's no math there.

1599
01:50:43.860 --> 01:50:45.820
I'm not leaving this rock
with one civilian on it.

1600
01:50:45.860 --> 01:50:47.305
I didn't say we should leave.

1601
01:50:50.140 --> 01:50:51.949
There's worse ways to go.

1602
01:50:57.420 --> 01:50:59.866
Where else am I gonna get
a view like this?

1603
01:51:00.740 --> 01:51:03.346
<i>Glad
you like the view. Romanoff.</i>

1604
01:51:03.460 --> 01:51:05.064
<i>It's about to get better.</i>

1605
01:51:29.180 --> 01:51:30.386
<i>Nice. right?</i>

1606
01:51:30.500 --> 01:51:32.946
Pulled her out of mothballs
with a couple of old friends.

1607
01:51:33.100 --> 01:51:34.750
She's dusty. but she'll do.

1608
01:51:35.100 --> 01:51:36.545
Fury. you son of a bitch.

1609
01:51:36.700 --> 01:51:38.987
Ooh! You kiss your mother
with that mouth?

1610
01:51:39.100 --> 01:51:41.307
Altitude is 18.000 and climbing.

1611
01:51:41.460 --> 01:51:42.985
Lifeboats secure to deploy.

1612
01:51:43.100 --> 01:51:45.785
Disengage in three. two...

1613
01:51:46.980 --> 01:51:47.981
Take them out.

1614
01:51:57.660 --> 01:51:59.185
This is S.H.I.E.L.D.?

1615
01:51:59.300 --> 01:52:01.746
This is what S.H.I.E.L.D.
is supposed to be.

1616
01:52:03.420 --> 01:52:04.831
This is not so bad.

1617
01:52:08.100 --> 01:52:09.431
Let's load them up.

1618
01:52:14.820 --> 01:52:18.661
Sir. we have multiple bogies
converging on our starboard flank.

1619
01:52:19.020 --> 01:52:20.226
Show 'em what we got.

1620
01:52:20.580 --> 01:52:21.581
You're up.

1621
01:52:26.860 --> 01:52:27.861
Yes!

1622
01:52:28.100 --> 01:52:29.864
Now this is gonna be a good story.

1623
01:52:32.500 --> 01:52:34.582
Yup. If you live to tell it.

1624
01:52:34.740 --> 01:52:36.742
You think I can't hold my own?

1625
01:52:36.860 --> 01:52:38.460
We get through this. I'll hold your own.

1626
01:52:38.540 --> 01:52:40.383
You had to make it weird.

1627
01:52:45.220 --> 01:52:48.190
I got about 50 to 100 more
coming in after this group.

1628
01:53:05.140 --> 01:53:06.551
Here we go. Here we go. Let's move.

1629
01:53:06.900 --> 01:53:07.981
Let's go. everyone!

1630
01:53:10.500 --> 01:53:12.502
Number six boat is topped and locked...

1631
01:53:12.620 --> 01:53:15.021
Or stocked... Topped...

1632
01:53:15.540 --> 01:53:16.985
It's full of people.

1633
01:53:18.740 --> 01:53:19.821
Incoming!

1634
01:53:22.860 --> 01:53:23.907
Oh. God!

1635
01:53:34.420 --> 01:53:35.660
<i>You think
you're saving anyone?</i>

1636
01:53:37.540 --> 01:53:39.542
I turn that key and
drop this rock a little early

1637
01:53:39.700 --> 01:53:41.782
and it's still billions dead.

1638
01:53:42.260 --> 01:53:43.421
Even you can't stop that.

1639
01:53:43.580 --> 01:53:45.981
I am Thor. son of Odin.

1640
01:53:46.100 --> 01:53:48.421
and as long as
there is life in my breast...

1641
01:53:48.540 --> 01:53:52.101
I am running out of things to say!
Are you ready?

1642
01:53:59.780 --> 01:54:00.906
It's terribly well-balanced.

1643
01:54:01.260 --> 01:54:04.742
Well. if there's too much weight.
you lose power on the swing. so...

1644
01:54:05.700 --> 01:54:08.351
I got it. Create a heat seal.

1645
01:54:08.780 --> 01:54:09.827
I could...

1646
01:54:09.900 --> 01:54:12.301
I could supercharge
the spire from below.

1647
01:54:12.460 --> 01:54:13.507
<i>Running numbers.</i>

1648
01:54:23.620 --> 01:54:25.304
<i>A heat seal could work
with enough power.</i>

1649
01:54:25.780 --> 01:54:27.782
- Thor. I got a plan.
<i>- We're out of time.</i>

1650
01:54:27.980 --> 01:54:29.186
<i>They're coming for the core.</i>

1651
01:54:29.300 --> 01:54:31.109
Rhodey. get the rest of the people
on board that carrier.

1652
01:54:31.260 --> 01:54:34.469
- On it.
- Avengers. time to work for a living.

1653
01:54:43.580 --> 01:54:44.820
- Are you good?
- Yeah.

1654
01:54:46.300 --> 01:54:47.347
Romanoff.

1655
01:54:47.500 --> 01:54:49.901
You and Banner better not be
playing "hide the zucchini."

1656
01:54:49.980 --> 01:54:51.061
<i>Relax. shellhead.</i>

1657
01:54:51.460 --> 01:54:52.905
Not all of us can fly.

1658
01:54:58.660 --> 01:55:00.344
- What's the drill?
- This is the drill.

1659
01:55:00.500 --> 01:55:02.662
If Ultron gets a hand
on the core. we lose.

1660
01:55:07.260 --> 01:55:09.262
Is that the best you can do?

1661
01:55:19.140 --> 01:55:20.710
You had to ask.

1662
01:55:20.820 --> 01:55:23.141
This is the best I can do.

1663
01:55:23.260 --> 01:55:24.910
This is exactly what I wanted.

1664
01:55:25.260 --> 01:55:26.591
All of you

1665
01:55:26.700 --> 01:55:28.350
against all of me.

1666
01:55:28.620 --> 01:55:30.827
How can you possibly hope to stop me?

1667
01:55:31.700 --> 01:55:33.543
Well. like the old man said...

1668
01:55:34.860 --> 01:55:35.861
Together.

1669
01:57:04.780 --> 01:57:07.181
You know. with the benefit of hindsight...

1670
01:57:16.460 --> 01:57:17.461
They'll try to leave the city.

1671
01:57:17.620 --> 01:57:19.304
We can't let them.
not even one. Rhodey.

1672
01:57:19.660 --> 01:57:20.741
I'm on it.

1673
01:57:21.140 --> 01:57:22.505
No. I didn't say you could leave.

1674
01:57:23.140 --> 01:57:25.222
War Machine coming at you! Right...

1675
01:57:31.620 --> 01:57:32.985
Okay. what?

1676
01:57:33.220 --> 01:57:35.222
We gotta move out.
Even I can tell the air is getting thin.

1677
01:57:35.380 --> 01:57:36.666
You guys get to the boats.

1678
01:57:36.820 --> 01:57:38.660
I'll sweep for stragglers.
Be right behind you.

1679
01:57:38.820 --> 01:57:41.266
- What about the core?
- I'll protect it.

1680
01:57:43.060 --> 01:57:44.221
It's my job.

1681
01:57:45.340 --> 01:57:46.501
Nat.

1682
01:57:46.780 --> 01:57:47.781
This way.

1683
01:57:52.180 --> 01:57:53.341
Get the people on the boats.

1684
01:57:53.500 --> 01:57:54.501
I'm not going to leave you here.

1685
01:57:54.660 --> 01:57:55.707
I can handle this.

1686
01:57:58.020 --> 01:57:59.260
Come back for me
when everyone else is off.

1687
01:57:59.500 --> 01:58:00.990
Not before.

1688
01:58:01.620 --> 01:58:02.746
You understand?

1689
01:58:03.780 --> 01:58:05.464
You know.
I'm 12 minutes older than you.

1690
01:58:05.860 --> 01:58:06.941
Go.

1691
01:58:08.500 --> 01:58:10.025
<i>Boss. power levels are way below...</i>

1692
01:58:10.140 --> 01:58:12.302
Reroute everything.
We get one shot at this.

1693
01:58:17.260 --> 01:58:18.546
I know what I need to do.

1694
01:58:18.860 --> 01:58:19.907
The dining room.

1695
01:58:20.180 --> 01:58:21.386
If I knock out that east wall.

1696
01:58:22.100 --> 01:58:23.740
it'd make a nice workspace
for Laura. huh?

1697
01:58:25.220 --> 01:58:26.381
Put up some baffling.

1698
01:58:26.500 --> 01:58:28.781
She can't hear the kids running around.
What do you think?

1699
01:58:28.820 --> 01:58:29.901
You guys always eat
in the kitchen anyway.

1700
01:58:30.060 --> 01:58:31.585
No one eats in a dining room.

1701
01:58:37.260 --> 01:58:38.380
We don't have a lot of time.

1702
01:58:38.980 --> 01:58:40.948
So get your ass on a boat.

1703
01:58:53.900 --> 01:58:55.026
Hey. big guy.

1704
01:58:56.820 --> 01:58:58.584
Sun's getting real low.

1705
01:58:59.100 --> 01:59:01.751
You're safe now.
You're gonna be okay. Buckle up.

1706
01:59:04.300 --> 01:59:05.870
Secure your gear. find a seat.

1707
01:59:05.980 --> 01:59:07.266
Costel!

1708
01:59:08.340 --> 01:59:09.466
We were in the market.

1709
01:59:09.580 --> 01:59:10.627
Costel!

1710
01:59:25.340 --> 01:59:27.388
Thor. I'm gonna
need you back in the church.

1711
01:59:27.500 --> 01:59:28.945
- Is this the last of them?
- Yeah.

1712
01:59:29.380 --> 01:59:31.661
- Everyone else is on the carrier.
<i>- You know. this works.</i>

1713
01:59:32.260 --> 01:59:33.671
we maybe don't walk away.

1714
01:59:34.380 --> 01:59:35.381
Maybe not.

1715
01:59:54.620 --> 01:59:58.147
<i>I got no strings. so I have fun</i>

1716
01:59:58.620 --> 02:00:01.305
<i>I'm not tied up to anyone</i>

1717
02:00:02.900 --> 02:00:04.231
Come on. Time to go.

1718
02:00:36.660 --> 02:00:38.708
You didn't see that coming?

1719
02:01:34.980 --> 02:01:36.744
For God's sake.

1720
02:01:53.020 --> 02:01:54.784
- Zrinka!
- Costel! Baby!

1721
02:02:07.260 --> 02:02:08.261
No. no. I'm fine.

1722
02:02:08.420 --> 02:02:09.421
Fine.

1723
02:02:11.260 --> 02:02:13.308
It's been a long day.

1724
02:02:27.860 --> 02:02:29.066
Wanda.

1725
02:02:29.780 --> 02:02:33.023
If you stay here. you'll die.

1726
02:02:34.620 --> 02:02:35.985
I just did.

1727
02:02:36.780 --> 02:02:38.544
Do you know how it felt?

1728
02:02:52.620 --> 02:02:54.987
It felt like that.

1729
02:03:29.980 --> 02:03:31.630
Thor. on my mark.

1730
02:03:46.700 --> 02:03:47.701
Now!

1731
02:04:15.700 --> 02:04:18.146
<i>Hey. big guy. We did it.</i>

1732
02:04:19.180 --> 02:04:20.864
<i>The job is finished.</i>

1733
02:04:21.060 --> 02:04:23.745
<i>Now I need you to turn
this bird around. okay?</i>

1734
02:04:28.060 --> 02:04:29.869
We can't track you in stealth mode.

1735
02:04:31.980 --> 02:04:34.108
<i>So help me out. I need you...</i>

1736
02:05:19.780 --> 02:05:20.781
You're afraid.

1737
02:05:21.780 --> 02:05:22.861
Of you?

1738
02:05:23.540 --> 02:05:24.701
Of death.

1739
02:05:25.420 --> 02:05:27.229
You're the last one.

1740
02:05:27.460 --> 02:05:29.906
You were supposed to be the last.

1741
02:05:30.140 --> 02:05:32.427
Stark asked for a saviour

1742
02:05:33.460 --> 02:05:35.144
and settled for a slave.

1743
02:05:35.260 --> 02:05:37.661
I suppose we are both disappointments.

1744
02:05:40.140 --> 02:05:41.380
I suppose we are.

1745
02:05:42.100 --> 02:05:43.261
Humans are odd.

1746
02:05:45.100 --> 02:05:48.741
They think order and chaos
are somehow opposites

1747
02:05:50.500 --> 02:05:51.831
and try to control what won't be.

1748
02:05:53.540 --> 02:05:55.986
But there is grace in their failings.

1749
02:05:56.300 --> 02:05:58.223
I think you missed that.

1750
02:05:58.900 --> 02:05:59.981
They're doomed.

1751
02:06:00.900 --> 02:06:01.947
Yes.

1752
02:06:06.180 --> 02:06:09.104
But a thing isn't beautiful
because it lasts.

1753
02:06:11.180 --> 02:06:13.182
It's a privilege to be among them.

1754
02:06:13.420 --> 02:06:15.946
You're unbearably naive.

1755
02:06:16.220 --> 02:06:17.426
Well...

1756
02:06:19.500 --> 02:06:21.548
I was born yesterday.

1757
02:07:34.180 --> 02:07:36.262
<i>Look! Say hi to Auntie Nat!</i>

1758
02:07:37.620 --> 02:07:38.621
Fat.

1759
02:07:39.740 --> 02:07:41.100
One of our tech boys flagged this.

1760
02:07:42.220 --> 02:07:44.382
Splashed down in the Banda Sea.

1761
02:07:45.500 --> 02:07:47.025
Could be the Quinjet.

1762
02:07:47.380 --> 02:07:50.750
But with Stark's stealth tech.
we still can't track the damn thing.

1763
02:07:52.300 --> 02:07:53.665
Right.

1764
02:07:54.100 --> 02:07:56.341
Probably jumped out and swam to Fiji.

1765
02:07:57.620 --> 02:07:59.509
He'll send a postcard.

1766
02:07:59.780 --> 02:08:01.509
"Wish you were here."

1767
02:08:03.460 --> 02:08:06.748
You sent me to recruit him
way back when.

1768
02:08:08.580 --> 02:08:11.151
Did you know then
what was gonna happen?

1769
02:08:13.340 --> 02:08:15.263
You never know.

1770
02:08:15.460 --> 02:08:18.987
You hope for the best.
then make do with what you get.

1771
02:08:19.460 --> 02:08:20.950
I got a great team.

1772
02:08:22.060 --> 02:08:24.028
Nothing lasts forever.

1773
02:08:24.300 --> 02:08:26.348
Trouble. Ms Romanoff.

1774
02:08:26.580 --> 02:08:29.948
No matter who wins or loses.
trouble still comes around.

1775
02:08:33.820 --> 02:08:35.026
<i>The rules have changed.</i>

1776
02:08:35.220 --> 02:08:36.824
We're dealing with something new.

1777
02:08:36.980 --> 02:08:38.266
The Vision is artificial intelligence.

1778
02:08:38.380 --> 02:08:40.303
- A machine.
- So. it doesn't count?

1779
02:08:40.500 --> 02:08:42.309
No. it's not like
a person lifting the hammer.

1780
02:08:42.580 --> 02:08:44.230
Right. different rules for us.

1781
02:08:44.460 --> 02:08:45.507
- Nice guy. Artificial.
- Thank you.

1782
02:08:45.700 --> 02:08:48.590
He can wield the hammer.
he can keep the Mind Stone.

1783
02:08:49.500 --> 02:08:51.582
It's safe with the Vision.

1784
02:08:51.820 --> 02:08:54.346
And these days. safe is in short supply.

1785
02:08:56.380 --> 02:08:58.348
But if you put the hammer
in an elevator...

1786
02:08:58.460 --> 02:09:00.340
- It would still go up.
- Elevator's not worthy.

1787
02:09:00.380 --> 02:09:02.189
I'm gonna miss these little talks of ours.

1788
02:09:02.340 --> 02:09:03.865
Not if you don't leave.

1789
02:09:04.100 --> 02:09:05.829
I have no choice.

1790
02:09:06.060 --> 02:09:08.222
The Mind Stone is the fourth
of the Infinity Stones

1791
02:09:08.340 --> 02:09:09.751
to show up in the last few years.

1792
02:09:09.860 --> 02:09:11.430
It's not a coincidence.

1793
02:09:12.260 --> 02:09:14.024
Someone has been playing
an intricate game

1794
02:09:14.180 --> 02:09:15.830
and has made pawns of us.

1795
02:09:15.940 --> 02:09:17.829
And once all these pieces
are in position...

1796
02:09:17.940 --> 02:09:19.351
Triple Yahtzee.

1797
02:09:19.580 --> 02:09:21.025
You think you can find out
what's coming?

1798
02:09:21.140 --> 02:09:22.221
I do.

1799
02:09:23.060 --> 02:09:24.550
Besides this one.

1800
02:09:24.660 --> 02:09:27.027
there's nothing that can't be explained.

1801
02:09:34.340 --> 02:09:36.866
That man has no regard
for lawn maintenance.

1802
02:09:40.020 --> 02:09:42.626
I'm gonna miss him. though.
And you're gonna miss me.

1803
02:09:42.740 --> 02:09:44.310
There's gonna be a lot of manful tears.

1804
02:09:46.500 --> 02:09:48.150
I will miss you. Tony.

1805
02:09:48.380 --> 02:09:49.381
Yeah?

1806
02:09:49.540 --> 02:09:51.986
Well. it's time for me to tap out.

1807
02:09:52.220 --> 02:09:54.382
Maybe I should take a page
out of Barton's book.

1808
02:09:54.540 --> 02:09:57.464
Build Pepper a farm.
hope nobody blows it up.

1809
02:09:58.260 --> 02:09:59.421
The simple life.

1810
02:09:59.700 --> 02:10:01.987
- You'll get there one day.
- I don't know.

1811
02:10:02.220 --> 02:10:04.621
Family. stability...

1812
02:10:05.780 --> 02:10:08.909
The guy who wanted all that
went in the ice 75 years ago.

1813
02:10:10.420 --> 02:10:12.263
I think someone else came out.

1814
02:10:16.220 --> 02:10:17.301
You all right?

1815
02:10:19.980 --> 02:10:21.425
I'm home.

1816
02:10:29.340 --> 02:10:32.105
You wanna keep staring at the wall.
or do you wanna go to work?

1817
02:10:32.260 --> 02:10:33.591
I mean. it's a pretty interesting wall.

1818
02:10:33.780 --> 02:10:36.784
I thought you and Tony were
still gazing into each other's eyes.

1819
02:10:36.860 --> 02:10:37.907
How do we look?

1820
02:10:38.140 --> 02:10:40.427
Well. we're not the '27 Yankees.

1821
02:10:40.580 --> 02:10:42.264
We got some hitters.

1822
02:10:42.420 --> 02:10:44.821
They're good. They're not a team.

1823
02:10:44.980 --> 02:10:46.630
Let's beat them into shape.

1824
02:11:05.100 --> 02:11:06.625
Avengers...

1825
02:13:25.460 --> 02:13:26.905
Fine.

1826
02:13:28.340 --> 02:13:30.183
I'll do it myself.
